div.cell {
  /* Old browsers */
  display: -webkit-box;
  -webkit-box-orient: vertical;
  -webkit-box-align: stretch;
  display: -moz-box;

  border-radius: 2px;

  -webkit-box-sizing: border-box;
  border-width: 1px;
  border-style: solid;
  border-color: transparent;
  width: 100%;
  padding: 5px;
  /* This acts as a spacer between cells, that is outside the border */
  margin: 0px;
  outline: none;
  position: relative;
  overflow: visible;
}
div.cell:before {
  position: absolute;

  width: 5px;
  height: calc(100% +  2px);
  content: '';
  background: transparent;
}

}

}

.prompt {
  /* This needs to be wide enough for 3 digit prompt numbers: In[100]: */
  min-width: 14ex;
  /* This padding is tuned to match the padding on the CodeMirror editor. */
  padding: 0.4em;
  margin: 0px;
  font-family: monospace;
  text-align: right;
  /* This has to match that of the the CodeMirror class line-height below */
  line-height: 1.21429em;
  /* Don't highlight prompt number selection */
  -webkit-touch-callout: none;
  -webkit-user-select: none;
  -khtml-user-select: none;
  -moz-user-select: none;
  -ms-user-select: none;
  user-select: none;
  /* Use default cursor */
  cursor: default;
}
@media (max-width: 540px) {

}
div.inner_cell {

div.input_area {

   is no content in the output_subarea and the prompt. The main purpose of this is

  padding-top: 0;

}

/* The following gets added to the <head> if it is detected that the user has a
 * monospace font with inconsistent normal/bold/italic height.  See
 * notebookmain.js.  Such fonts will have keywords vertically offset with
 * respect to the rest of the text.  The user should select a better font.
 * See: https://github.com/ipython/ipython/issues/1503
 *
 * .CodeMirror span {
 *      vertical-align: bottom;
 * }
 */
.CodeMirror {
  line-height: 1.21429em;
  /* Changed from 1em to our global default */
  font-size: 14px;
  height: auto;
  /* Changed to auto to autogrow */
  background: none;
  /* Changed from white to allow our bg to show through */
}
.CodeMirror-scroll {
  /*  The CodeMirror docs are a bit fuzzy on if overflow-y should be hidden or visible.*/
  /*  We have found that if it is visible, vertical scrollbars appear with font size changes.*/
  overflow-y: hidden;
  overflow-x: auto;
}
.CodeMirror-lines {
  /* In CM2, this used to be 0.4em, but in CM3 it went to 4px. We need the em value because */
  /* we have set a different line-height and want this to scale with that. */
  /* Note that this should set vertical padding only, since CodeMirror assumes
       that horizontal padding will be set on CodeMirror pre */
  padding: 0.4em 0;
}
.CodeMirror-linenumber {
  padding: 0 8px 0 4px;
}
.CodeMirror-gutters {
  border-bottom-left-radius: 2px;
  border-top-left-radius: 2px;
}
.CodeMirror pre {
  /* In CM3 this went to 4px from 0 in CM2. This sets horizontal padding only,
    use .CodeMirror-lines for vertical */
  padding: 0 0.4em;
  border: 0;
  border-radius: 0;
}
.CodeMirror-cursor {
  border-left: 1.4px solid black;
}
@media screen and (min-width: 2138px) and (max-width: 4319px) {
  .CodeMirror-cursor {
    border-left: 2px solid black;
  }
}
@media screen and (min-width: 4320px) {
  .CodeMirror-cursor {

}

div.output_scroll {
  /* ideally, this would be max-height, but FF barfs all over that */
  height: 24em;

  width: 100%;

  border-radius: 2px;

<h1 id="Read-in-the-data">Read in the data<a class="anchor-link" href="#Read-in-the-data">¶</a></h1>
</div>
</div>
</div>
<div class="cell border-box-sizing code_cell rendered">
<div class="input">
<div class="prompt input_prompt">In [23]:</div>
<div class="inner_cell">
    <div class="input_area">
<div class=" highlight hl-ipython3"><pre><span></span><span class="kn">import</span> <span class="nn">pandas</span> <span class="k">as</span> <span class="nn">pd</span>
<span class="kn">import</span> <span class="nn">numpy</span>
<span class="kn">import</span> <span class="nn">re</span>

<span class="n">data_files</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="p">[</span>
    <span class="s2">"ap_2010.csv"</span><span class="p">,</span>
    <span class="s2">"class_size.csv"</span><span class="p">,</span>
    <span class="s2">"demographics.csv"</span><span class="p">,</span>
    <span class="s2">"graduation.csv"</span><span class="p">,</span>
    <span class="s2">"hs_directory.csv"</span><span class="p">,</span>
    <span class="s2">"sat_results.csv"</span>
<span class="p">]</span>

<span class="n">data</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="p">{}</span>

<span class="k">for</span> <span class="n">f</span> <span class="ow">in</span> <span class="n">data_files</span><span class="p">:</span>
    <span class="n">d</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">pd</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">read_csv</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="s2">"schools/</span><span class="si">{0}</span><span class="s2">"</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">format</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">f</span><span class="p">))</span>
    <span class="n">data</span><span class="p">[</span><span class="n">f</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">replace</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="s2">".csv"</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="s2">""</span><span class="p">)]</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">d</span>
</pre></div>

    </div>
</div>
</div>

</div>
<div class="cell border-box-sizing text_cell rendered"><div class="prompt input_prompt">
</div><div class="inner_cell">
<div class="text_cell_render border-box-sizing rendered_html">
<h1 id="Read-in-the-surveys">Read in the surveys<a class="anchor-link" href="#Read-in-the-surveys">¶</a></h1>
</div>
</div>
</div>
<div class="cell border-box-sizing code_cell rendered">
<div class="input">
<div class="prompt input_prompt">In [24]:</div>
<div class="inner_cell">
    <div class="input_area">
<div class=" highlight hl-ipython3"><pre><span></span><span class="n">all_survey</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">pd</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">read_csv</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="s2">"schools/survey_all.txt"</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">delimiter</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="s2">"</span><span class="se">\t</span><span class="s2">"</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">encoding</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="s1">'windows-1252'</span><span class="p">)</span>
<span class="n">d75_survey</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">pd</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">read_csv</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="s2">"schools/survey_d75.txt"</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">delimiter</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="s2">"</span><span class="se">\t</span><span class="s2">"</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">encoding</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="s1">'windows-1252'</span><span class="p">)</span>
<span class="n">survey</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">pd</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">concat</span><span class="p">([</span><span class="n">all_survey</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">d75_survey</span><span class="p">],</span> <span class="n">axis</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="mi">0</span><span class="p">)</span>

<span class="n">survey</span><span class="p">[</span><span class="s2">"DBN"</span><span class="p">]</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">survey</span><span class="p">[</span><span class="s2">"dbn"</span><span class="p">]</span>

<span class="n">survey_fields</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="p">[</span>
    <span class="s2">"DBN"</span><span class="p">,</span> 
    <span class="s2">"rr_s"</span><span class="p">,</span> 
    <span class="s2">"rr_t"</span><span class="p">,</span> 
    <span class="s2">"rr_p"</span><span class="p">,</span> 
    <span class="s2">"N_s"</span><span class="p">,</span> 
    <span class="s2">"N_t"</span><span class="p">,</span> 
    <span class="s2">"N_p"</span><span class="p">,</span> 
    <span class="s2">"saf_p_11"</span><span class="p">,</span> 
    <span class="s2">"com_p_11"</span><span class="p">,</span> 
    <span class="s2">"eng_p_11"</span><span class="p">,</span> 
    <span class="s2">"aca_p_11"</span><span class="p">,</span> 
    <span class="s2">"saf_t_11"</span><span class="p">,</span> 
    <span class="s2">"com_t_11"</span><span class="p">,</span> 
    <span class="s2">"eng_t_11"</span><span class="p">,</span> 
    <span class="s2">"aca_t_11"</span><span class="p">,</span> 
    <span class="s2">"saf_s_11"</span><span class="p">,</span> 
    <span class="s2">"com_s_11"</span><span class="p">,</span> 
    <span class="s2">"eng_s_11"</span><span class="p">,</span> 
    <span class="s2">"aca_s_11"</span><span class="p">,</span> 
    <span class="s2">"saf_tot_11"</span><span class="p">,</span> 
    <span class="s2">"com_tot_11"</span><span class="p">,</span> 
    <span class="s2">"eng_tot_11"</span><span class="p">,</span> 
    <span class="s2">"aca_tot_11"</span><span class="p">,</span>
<span class="p">]</span>
<span class="n">survey</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">survey</span><span class="p">[</span><span class="n">survey_fields</span><span class="p">]</span>
<span class="n">data</span><span class="p">[</span><span class="s2">"survey"</span><span class="p">]</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">survey</span>
</pre></div>

    </div>
</div>
</div>

</div>
<div class="cell border-box-sizing text_cell rendered"><div class="prompt input_prompt">
</div><div class="inner_cell">
<div class="text_cell_render border-box-sizing rendered_html">

</div>
</div>
</div>
<div class="cell border-box-sizing code_cell rendered">
<div class="input">
<div class="prompt input_prompt">In [25]:</div>
<div class="inner_cell">
    <div class="input_area">
<div class=" highlight hl-ipython3"><pre><span></span><span class="n">data</span><span class="p">[</span><span class="s2">"hs_directory"</span><span class="p">][</span><span class="s2">"DBN"</span><span class="p">]</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">data</span><span class="p">[</span><span class="s2">"hs_directory"</span><span class="p">][</span><span class="s2">"dbn"</span><span class="p">]</span>

<span class="k">def</span> <span class="nf">pad_csd</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">num</span><span class="p">):</span>
    <span class="n">string_representation</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="nb">str</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">num</span><span class="p">)</span>
    <span class="k">if</span> <span class="nb">len</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">string_representation</span><span class="p">)</span> <span class="o">></span> <span class="mi">1</span><span class="p">:</span>
        <span class="k">return</span> <span class="n">string_representation</span>
    <span class="k">else</span><span class="p">:</span>
        <span class="k">return</span> <span class="s2">"0"</span> <span class="o">+</span> <span class="n">string_representation</span>
    
<span class="n">data</span><span class="p">[</span><span class="s2">"class_size"</span><span class="p">][</span><span class="s2">"padded_csd"</span><span class="p">]</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">data</span><span class="p">[</span><span class="s2">"class_size"</span><span class="p">][</span><span class="s2">"CSD"</span><span class="p">]</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">apply</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">pad_csd</span><span class="p">)</span>
<span class="n">data</span><span class="p">[</span><span class="s2">"class_size"</span><span class="p">][</span><span class="s2">"DBN"</span><span class="p">]</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">data</span><span class="p">[</span><span class="s2">"class_size"</span><span class="p">][</span><span class="s2">"padded_csd"</span><span class="p">]</span> <span class="o">+</span> <span class="n">data</span><span class="p">[</span><span class="s2">"class_size"</span><span class="p">][</span><span class="s2">"SCHOOL CODE"</span><span class="p">]</span>
</pre></div>

</div>

</div>
<div class="cell border-box-sizing text_cell rendered"><div class="prompt input_prompt">
</div><div class="inner_cell">
<div class="text_cell_render border-box-sizing rendered_html">
<h1 id="Convert-columns-to-numeric">Convert columns to numeric<a class="anchor-link" href="#Convert-columns-to-numeric">¶</a></h1>
</div>
</div>
</div>
<div class="cell border-box-sizing code_cell rendered">
<div class="input">
<div class="prompt input_prompt">In [26]:</div>
<div class="inner_cell">
    <div class="input_area">
<div class=" highlight hl-ipython3"><pre><span></span><span class="n">cols</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="p">[</span><span class="s1">'SAT Math Avg. Score'</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="s1">'SAT Critical Reading Avg. Score'</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="s1">'SAT Writing Avg. Score'</span><span class="p">]</span>
<span class="k">for</span> <span class="n">c</span> <span class="ow">in</span> <span class="n">cols</span><span class="p">:</span>
    <span class="n">data</span><span class="p">[</span><span class="s2">"sat_results"</span><span class="p">][</span><span class="n">c</span><span class="p">]</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">pd</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">to_numeric</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">data</span><span class="p">[</span><span class="s2">"sat_results"</span><span class="p">][</span><span class="n">c</span><span class="p">],</span> <span class="n">errors</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="s2">"coerce"</span><span class="p">)</span>

<span class="n">data</span><span class="p">[</span><span class="s1">'sat_results'</span><span class="p">][</span><span class="s1">'sat_score'</span><span class="p">]</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">data</span><span class="p">[</span><span class="s1">'sat_results'</span><span class="p">][</span><span class="n">cols</span><span class="p">[</span><span class="mi">0</span><span class="p">]]</span> <span class="o">+</span> <span class="n">data</span><span class="p">[</span><span class="s1">'sat_results'</span><span class="p">][</span><span class="n">cols</span><span class="p">[</span><span class="mi">1</span><span class="p">]]</span> <span class="o">+</span> <span class="n">data</span><span class="p">[</span><span class="s1">'sat_results'</span><span class="p">][</span><span class="n">cols</span><span class="p">[</span><span class="mi">2</span><span class="p">]]</span>

<span class="k">def</span> <span class="nf">find_lat</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">loc</span><span class="p">):</span>
    <span class="n">coords</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">re</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">findall</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="s2">"\(.+, .+\)"</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">loc</span><span class="p">)</span>
    <span class="n">lat</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">coords</span><span class="p">[</span><span class="mi">0</span><span class="p">]</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">split</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="s2">","</span><span class="p">)[</span><span class="mi">0</span><span class="p">]</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">replace</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="s2">"("</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="s2">""</span><span class="p">)</span>
    <span class="k">return</span> <span class="n">lat</span>

<span class="k">def</span> <span class="nf">find_lon</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">loc</span><span class="p">):</span>
    <span class="n">coords</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">re</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">findall</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="s2">"\(.+, .+\)"</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">loc</span><span class="p">)</span>
    <span class="n">lon</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">coords</span><span class="p">[</span><span class="mi">0</span><span class="p">]</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">split</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="s2">","</span><span class="p">)[</span><span class="mi">1</span><span class="p">]</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">replace</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="s2">")"</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="s2">""</span><span class="p">)</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">strip</span><span class="p">()</span>
    <span class="k">return</span> <span class="n">lon</span>

<span class="n">data</span><span class="p">[</span><span class="s2">"hs_directory"</span><span class="p">][</span><span class="s2">"lat"</span><span class="p">]</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">data</span><span class="p">[</span><span class="s2">"hs_directory"</span><span class="p">][</span><span class="s2">"Location 1"</span><span class="p">]</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">apply</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">find_lat</span><span class="p">)</span>
<span class="n">data</span><span class="p">[</span><span class="s2">"hs_directory"</span><span class="p">][</span><span class="s2">"lon"</span><span class="p">]</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">data</span><span class="p">[</span><span class="s2">"hs_directory"</span><span class="p">][</span><span class="s2">"Location 1"</span><span class="p">]</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">apply</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">find_lon</span><span class="p">)</span>

<span class="n">data</span><span class="p">[</span><span class="s2">"hs_directory"</span><span class="p">][</span><span class="s2">"lat"</span><span class="p">]</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">pd</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">to_numeric</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">data</span><span class="p">[</span><span class="s2">"hs_directory"</span><span class="p">][</span><span class="s2">"lat"</span><span class="p">],</span> <span class="n">errors</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="s2">"coerce"</span><span class="p">)</span>
<span class="n">data</span><span class="p">[</span><span class="s2">"hs_directory"</span><span class="p">][</span><span class="s2">"lon"</span><span class="p">]</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">pd</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">to_numeric</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">data</span><span class="p">[</span><span class="s2">"hs_directory"</span><span class="p">][</span><span class="s2">"lon"</span><span class="p">],</span> <span class="n">errors</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="s2">"coerce"</span><span class="p">)</span>
</pre></div>

    </div>
</div>
</div>

</div>
<div class="cell border-box-sizing text_cell rendered"><div class="prompt input_prompt">
</div><div class="inner_cell">
<div class="text_cell_render border-box-sizing rendered_html">
<h1 id="Condense-datasets">Condense datasets<a class="anchor-link" href="#Condense-datasets">¶</a></h1>
</div>
</div>
</div>
<div class="cell border-box-sizing code_cell rendered">
<div class="input">
<div class="prompt input_prompt">In [27]:</div>
<div class="inner_cell">
    <div class="input_area">
<div class=" highlight hl-ipython3"><pre><span></span><span class="n">class_size</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">data</span><span class="p">[</span><span class="s2">"class_size"</span><span class="p">]</span>
<span class="n">class_size</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">class_size</span><span class="p">[</span><span class="n">class_size</span><span class="p">[</span><span class="s2">"GRADE "</span><span class="p">]</span> <span class="o">==</span> <span class="s2">"09-12"</span><span class="p">]</span>
<span class="n">class_size</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">class_size</span><span class="p">[</span><span class="n">class_size</span><span class="p">[</span><span class="s2">"PROGRAM TYPE"</span><span class="p">]</span> <span class="o">==</span> <span class="s2">"GEN ED"</span><span class="p">]</span>

<span class="n">class_size</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">class_size</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">groupby</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="s2">"DBN"</span><span class="p">)</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">agg</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">numpy</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">mean</span><span class="p">)</span>
<span class="n">class_size</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">reset_index</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">inplace</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="kc">True</span><span class="p">)</span>
<span class="n">data</span><span class="p">[</span><span class="s2">"class_size"</span><span class="p">]</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">class_size</span>

<span class="n">data</span><span class="p">[</span><span class="s2">"demographics"</span><span class="p">]</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">data</span><span class="p">[</span><span class="s2">"demographics"</span><span class="p">][</span><span class="n">data</span><span class="p">[</span><span class="s2">"demographics"</span><span class="p">][</span><span class="s2">"schoolyear"</span><span class="p">]</span> <span class="o">==</span> <span class="mi">20112012</span><span class="p">]</span>

<span class="n">data</span><span class="p">[</span><span class="s2">"graduation"</span><span class="p">]</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">data</span><span class="p">[</span><span class="s2">"graduation"</span><span class="p">][</span><span class="n">data</span><span class="p">[</span><span class="s2">"graduation"</span><span class="p">][</span><span class="s2">"Cohort"</span><span class="p">]</span> <span class="o">==</span> <span class="s2">"2006"</span><span class="p">]</span>
<span class="n">data</span><span class="p">[</span><span class="s2">"graduation"</span><span class="p">]</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">data</span><span class="p">[</span><span class="s2">"graduation"</span><span class="p">][</span><span class="n">data</span><span class="p">[</span><span class="s2">"graduation"</span><span class="p">][</span><span class="s2">"Demographic"</span><span class="p">]</span> <span class="o">==</span> <span class="s2">"Total Cohort"</span><span class="p">]</span>
</pre></div>

    </div>
</div>
</div>

</div>
<div class="cell border-box-sizing text_cell rendered"><div class="prompt input_prompt">
</div><div class="inner_cell">
<div class="text_cell_render border-box-sizing rendered_html">
<h1 id="Convert-AP-scores-to-numeric">Convert AP scores to numeric<a class="anchor-link" href="#Convert-AP-scores-to-numeric">¶</a></h1>
</div>
</div>
</div>
<div class="cell border-box-sizing code_cell rendered">
<div class="input">
<div class="prompt input_prompt">In [28]:</div>
<div class="inner_cell">
    <div class="input_area">
<div class=" highlight hl-ipython3"><pre><span></span><span class="n">cols</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="p">[</span><span class="s1">'AP Test Takers '</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="s1">'Total Exams Taken'</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="s1">'Number of Exams with scores 3 4 or 5'</span><span class="p">]</span>

<span class="k">for</span> <span class="n">col</span> <span class="ow">in</span> <span class="n">cols</span><span class="p">:</span>
    <span class="n">data</span><span class="p">[</span><span class="s2">"ap_2010"</span><span class="p">][</span><span class="n">col</span><span class="p">]</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">pd</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">to_numeric</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">data</span><span class="p">[</span><span class="s2">"ap_2010"</span><span class="p">][</span><span class="n">col</span><span class="p">],</span> <span class="n">errors</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="s2">"coerce"</span><span class="p">)</span>
</pre></div>

    </div>
</div>
</div>

</div>
<div class="cell border-box-sizing text_cell rendered"><div class="prompt input_prompt">
</div><div class="inner_cell">
<div class="text_cell_render border-box-sizing rendered_html">
<h1 id="Combine-the-datasets">Combine the datasets<a class="anchor-link" href="#Combine-the-datasets">¶</a></h1>
</div>
</div>
</div>
<div class="cell border-box-sizing code_cell rendered">
<div class="input">
<div class="prompt input_prompt">In [29]:</div>
<div class="inner_cell">
    <div class="input_area">
<div class=" highlight hl-ipython3"><pre><span></span><span class="n">combined</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">data</span><span class="p">[</span><span class="s2">"sat_results"</span><span class="p">]</span>

<span class="n">combined</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">combined</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">merge</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">data</span><span class="p">[</span><span class="s2">"ap_2010"</span><span class="p">],</span> <span class="n">on</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="s2">"DBN"</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">how</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="s2">"left"</span><span class="p">)</span>
<span class="n">combined</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">combined</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">merge</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">data</span><span class="p">[</span><span class="s2">"graduation"</span><span class="p">],</span> <span class="n">on</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="s2">"DBN"</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">how</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="s2">"left"</span><span class="p">)</span>

<span class="n">to_merge</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="p">[</span><span class="s2">"class_size"</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="s2">"demographics"</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="s2">"survey"</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="s2">"hs_directory"</span><span class="p">]</span>

<span class="k">for</span> <span class="n">m</span> <span class="ow">in</span> <span class="n">to_merge</span><span class="p">:</span>
    <span class="n">combined</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">combined</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">merge</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">data</span><span class="p">[</span><span class="n">m</span><span class="p">],</span> <span class="n">on</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="s2">"DBN"</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">how</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="s2">"inner"</span><span class="p">)</span>

<span class="n">combined</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">combined</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">fillna</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">combined</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">mean</span><span class="p">())</span>
<span class="n">combined</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">combined</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">fillna</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="mi">0</span><span class="p">)</span>
</pre></div>

    </div>
</div>
</div>

</div>
<div class="cell border-box-sizing text_cell rendered"><div class="prompt input_prompt">
</div><div class="inner_cell">
<div class="text_cell_render border-box-sizing rendered_html">
<h1 id="Add-a-school-district-column-for-mapping">Add a school district column for mapping<a class="anchor-link" href="#Add-a-school-district-column-for-mapping">¶</a></h1>
</div>
</div>
</div>
<div class="cell border-box-sizing code_cell rendered">
<div class="input">
<div class="prompt input_prompt">In [30]:</div>
<div class="inner_cell">
    <div class="input_area">
<div class=" highlight hl-ipython3"><pre><span></span><span class="k">def</span> <span class="nf">get_first_two_chars</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">dbn</span><span class="p">):</span>
    <span class="k">return</span> <span class="n">dbn</span><span class="p">[</span><span class="mi">0</span><span class="p">:</span><span class="mi">2</span><span class="p">]</span>

<span class="n">combined</span><span class="p">[</span><span class="s2">"school_dist"</span><span class="p">]</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">combined</span><span class="p">[</span><span class="s2">"DBN"</span><span class="p">]</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">apply</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">get_first_two_chars</span><span class="p">)</span>
</pre></div>

    </div>
</div>
</div>

</div>
<div class="cell border-box-sizing text_cell rendered"><div class="prompt input_prompt">
</div><div class="inner_cell">
<div class="text_cell_render border-box-sizing rendered_html">

<span class="n">correlations</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">correlations</span><span class="p">[</span><span class="s2">"sat_score"</span><span class="p">]</span>

<div class="text_cell_render border-box-sizing rendered_html">
<p>There are high correlations between <code>N_s</code>, <code>N_t</code>, <code>N_p</code> and <code>sat_score</code>.  Since these columns are correlated with <code>total_enrollment</code>, it makes sense that they would be high.</p>
<p>It is more interesting that <code>rr_s</code>, the student response rate, or the percentage of students that completed the survey, correlates with <code>sat_score</code>.  This might make sense because students who are more likely to fill out surveys may be more likely to also be doing well academically.</p>
<p>How students and teachers percieved safety (<code>saf_t_11</code> and <code>saf_s_11</code>) correlate with <code>sat_score</code>.  This make sense, as it's hard to teach or learn in an unsafe environment.</p>
<p>The last interesting correlation is the <code>aca_s_11</code>, which indicates how the student perceives academic standards, correlates with <code>sat_score</code>, but this is not true for <code>aca_t_11</code>, how teachers perceive academic standards, or <code>aca_p_11</code>, how parents perceive academic standards.</p>

<div class="text_cell_render border-box-sizing rendered_html">
<p>There appears to be a correlation between SAT scores and safety, although it isn't thatstrong.  It looks like there are a few schools with extremely high SAT scores and high safety scores.  There are a few schools with low safety scores and low SAT scores.  No school with a safety score lower than <code>6.5</code> has an average SAT score higher than 1500 or so.</p>

<div class=" highlight hl-ipython3"><pre><span></span><span class="kn">import</span> <span class="nn">matplotlib.pyplot</span> <span class="k">as</span> <span class="nn">plt</span>
<span class="kn">from</span> <span class="nn">mpl_toolkits.basemap</span> <span class="kn">import</span> <span class="n">Basemap</span>

<span class="n">districts</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">combined</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">groupby</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="s2">"school_dist"</span><span class="p">)</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">agg</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">numpy</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">mean</span><span class="p">)</span>
<span class="n">districts</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">reset_index</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">inplace</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="kc">True</span><span class="p">)</span>

<span class="n">m</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">Basemap</span><span class="p">(</span>
    <span class="n">projection</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="s1">'merc'</span><span class="p">,</span> 
    <span class="n">llcrnrlat</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="mf">40.496044</span><span class="p">,</span> 
    <span class="n">urcrnrlat</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="mf">40.915256</span><span class="p">,</span> 
    <span class="n">llcrnrlon</span><span class="o">=-</span><span class="mf">74.255735</span><span class="p">,</span> 
    <span class="n">urcrnrlon</span><span class="o">=-</span><span class="mf">73.700272</span><span class="p">,</span>
    <span class="n">resolution</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="s1">'i'</span>
<span class="p">)</span>

<span class="n">m</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">drawmapboundary</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">fill_color</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="s1">'#85A6D9'</span><span class="p">)</span>
<span class="n">m</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">drawcoastlines</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">color</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="s1">'#6D5F47'</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">linewidth</span><span class="o">=.</span><span class="mi">4</span><span class="p">)</span>
<span class="n">m</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">drawrivers</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">color</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="s1">'#6D5F47'</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">linewidth</span><span class="o">=.</span><span class="mi">4</span><span class="p">)</span>

<span class="n">latitudes</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">districts</span><span class="p">[</span><span class="s2">"lat"</span><span class="p">]</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">tolist</span><span class="p">()</span>
<span class="n">m</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">scatter</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">longitudes</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">latitudes</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">s</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="mi">50</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">zorder</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="mi">2</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">latlon</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="kc">True</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">c</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="n">districts</span><span class="p">[</span><span class="s2">"saf_s_11"</span><span class="p">],</span> <span class="n">cmap</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="s2">"summer"</span><span class="p">)</span>

<p>It looks like a higher percentage of white or asian students at a school correlates positively with sat score, whereas a higher percentage of black or hispanic students correlates negatively with sat score.  This may be due to a lack of funding for schools in certain areas, which are more likely to have a higher percentage of black or hispanic students.</p>

<div class="text_cell_render border-box-sizing rendered_html">
<p>The schools listed above appear to primarily be geared towards recent immigrants to the US.  These schools have a lot of students who are learning English, which would explain the lower SAT scores.</p>

</div>
</div>
</div>
<div class="cell border-box-sizing code_cell rendered">

</div><div class="inner_cell">
<div class="text_cell_render border-box-sizing rendered_html">
<p>Many of the schools above appear to be specialized science and technology schools that receive extra funding, and only admit students who pass an entrance exam.  This doesn't explain the low <code>hispanic_per</code>, but it does explain why their students tend to do better on the SAT -- they are students from all over New York City who did well on a standardized test.</p>

<p>Based on the scatterplot, there doesn't seem to be any real correlation between <code>sat_score</code> and <code>female_per</code>.  However, there is a cluster of schools with a high percentage of females (<code>60</code> to <code>80</code>), and high SAT scores.</p>

<div class=" highlight hl-ipython3"><pre><span></span><span class="nb">print</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">combined</span><span class="p">[(</span><span class="n">combined</span><span class="p">[</span><span class="s2">"female_per"</span><span class="p">]</span> <span class="o">></span> <span class="mi">60</span><span class="p">)</span> <span class="o">&</span> <span class="p">(</span><span class="n">combined</span><span class="p">[</span><span class="s2">"sat_score"</span><span class="p">]</span> <span class="o">></span> <span class="mi">1700</span><span class="p">)][</span><span class="s2">"SCHOOL NAME"</span><span class="p">])</span>

<div class=" highlight hl-ipython3"><pre><span></span><span class="kn">import</span> <span class="nn">pandas</span> <span class="k">as</span> <span class="nn">pd</span>
<span class="n">pd</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">options</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">display</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">max_columns</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="mi">99</span>
<span class="n">chunk_iter</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">pd</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">read_csv</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="s1">'crunchbase-investments.csv'</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">chunksize</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="mi">5000</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">encoding</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="s1">'ISO-8859-1'</span><span class="p">)</span>
</pre></div>

</div><div class="inner_cell">

<p>Compute each column's missing value counts</p>

<div class=" highlight hl-ipython3"><pre><span></span><span class="n">mv_list</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="p">[]</span>
<span class="k">for</span> <span class="n">chunk</span> <span class="ow">in</span> <span class="n">chunk_iter</span><span class="p">:</span>
    <span class="n">mv_list</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">append</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">chunk</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">isnull</span><span class="p">()</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">sum</span><span class="p">())</span>
    
<span class="n">combined_mv_vc</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">pd</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">concat</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">mv_list</span><span class="p">)</span>
<span class="n">unique_combined_mv_vc</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">combined_mv_vc</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">groupby</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">combined_mv_vc</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">index</span><span class="p">)</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">sum</span><span class="p">()</span>

<h2 id="Selecting-Data-Types">Selecting Data Types<a class="anchor-link" href="#Selecting-Data-Types">¶</a></h2><p>Let's first determine which columns shift types across chunks. Note that we only lay the groundwork for this step.</p>

<div class="input">

    <div class="input_area">
<div class=" highlight hl-ipython3"><pre><span></span><span class="c1"># Key: Column name, Value: List of types</span>
<span class="n">col_types</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="p">{}</span>
<span class="n">chunk_iter</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">pd</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">read_csv</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="s1">'crunchbase-investments.csv'</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">chunksize</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="mi">5000</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">encoding</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="s1">'ISO-8859-1'</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">usecols</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="n">keep_cols</span><span class="p">)</span>

<span class="k">for</span> <span class="n">chunk</span> <span class="ow">in</span> <span class="n">chunk_iter</span><span class="p">:</span>
    <span class="k">for</span> <span class="n">col</span> <span class="ow">in</span> <span class="n">chunk</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">columns</span><span class="p">:</span>
        <span class="k">if</span> <span class="n">col</span> <span class="ow">not</span> <span class="ow">in</span> <span class="n">col_types</span><span class="p">:</span>
            <span class="n">col_types</span><span class="p">[</span><span class="n">col</span><span class="p">]</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="p">[</span><span class="nb">str</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">chunk</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">dtypes</span><span class="p">[</span><span class="n">col</span><span class="p">])]</span>
        <span class="k">else</span><span class="p">:</span>
            <span class="n">col_types</span><span class="p">[</span><span class="n">col</span><span class="p">]</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">append</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="nb">str</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">chunk</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">dtypes</span><span class="p">[</span><span class="n">col</span><span class="p">]))</span>
</pre></div>

    <span class="n">uniq_col_types</span><span class="p">[</span><span class="n">k</span><span class="p">]</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="nb">set</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">col_types</span><span class="p">[</span><span class="n">k</span><span class="p">])</span>

<div class="text_cell_render border-box-sizing rendered_html">
<h2 id="Loading-Chunks-Into-SQLite">Loading Chunks Into SQLite<a class="anchor-link" href="#Loading-Chunks-Into-SQLite">¶</a></h2>
</div>
</div>
</div>
<div class="cell border-box-sizing code_cell rendered">
<div class="input">
<div class="prompt input_prompt">In [94]:</div>
<div class="inner_cell">
    <div class="input_area">
<div class=" highlight hl-ipython3"><pre><span></span><span class="kn">import</span> <span class="nn">sqlite3</span>
<span class="n">conn</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">sqlite3</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">connect</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="s1">'crunchbase.db'</span><span class="p">)</span>
<span class="n">chunk_iter</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">pd</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">read_csv</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="s1">'crunchbase-investments.csv'</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">chunksize</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="mi">5000</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">encoding</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="s1">'ISO-8859-1'</span><span class="p">)</span>

<span class="k">for</span> <span class="n">chunk</span> <span class="ow">in</span> <span class="n">chunk_iter</span><span class="p">:</span>
    <span class="n">chunk</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">to_sql</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="s2">"investments"</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">conn</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">if_exists</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="s1">'append'</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">index</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="kc">False</span><span class="p">)</span>
</pre></div>

<h1 id="Stock-Price-Data">Stock Price Data<a class="anchor-link" href="#Stock-Price-Data">¶</a></h1>
</div>
</div>
</div>
<div class="cell border-box-sizing code_cell rendered">
<div class="input">
<div class="prompt input_prompt">In [45]:</div>
<div class="inner_cell">
    <div class="input_area">
<div class=" highlight hl-ipython3"><pre><span></span><span class="kn">import</span> <span class="nn">concurrent.futures</span>
<span class="kn">import</span> <span class="nn">os</span>

<span class="k">def</span> <span class="nf">read_file</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">filename</span><span class="p">):</span>
    <span class="k">with</span> <span class="nb">open</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">filename</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="s1">'r'</span><span class="p">)</span> <span class="k">as</span> <span class="n">f</span><span class="p">:</span>
        <span class="n">data</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">f</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">read</span><span class="p">()</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">strip</span><span class="p">()</span>
    <span class="n">key</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">filename</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">replace</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="s2">".csv"</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="s2">""</span><span class="p">)</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">replace</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="s2">"prices/"</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="s2">""</span><span class="p">)</span>
    <span class="n">data</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">data</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">split</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="s2">"</span><span class="se">\n</span><span class="s2">"</span><span class="p">)</span>
    <span class="n">data</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="p">[</span><span class="n">d</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">split</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="s2">","</span><span class="p">)</span> <span class="k">for</span> <span class="n">d</span> <span class="ow">in</span> <span class="n">data</span><span class="p">]</span>
    <span class="k">return</span> <span class="n">key</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">data</span>

<span class="n">results</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="p">[]</span>
<span class="n">pool</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">concurrent</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">futures</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">ProcessPoolExecutor</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">max_workers</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="mi">2</span><span class="p">)</span>
<span class="n">filenames</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="p">[</span><span class="s2">"prices/</span><span class="si">{}</span><span class="s2">"</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">format</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">f</span><span class="p">)</span> <span class="k">for</span> <span class="n">f</span> <span class="ow">in</span> <span class="n">os</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">listdir</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="s2">"prices"</span><span class="p">)]</span>
<span class="n">prices</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">pool</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">map</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">read_file</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">filenames</span><span class="p">)</span>
<span class="n">prices</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="nb">list</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">prices</span><span class="p">)</span>
<span class="n">prices</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="nb">dict</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">prices</span><span class="p">)</span>
</pre></div>

    </div>
</div>
</div>

</div>
<div class="cell border-box-sizing text_cell rendered"><div class="prompt input_prompt">
</div><div class="inner_cell">
<div class="text_cell_render border-box-sizing rendered_html">
<p>I chose to use a hash table, then a list, then another list.  This is because it closely mirrors the existing structure of the data.  It allows stock symbols to be easily looked up, and enables me to index values efficiently.</p>

</div>
</div>
</div>
<div class="cell border-box-sizing text_cell rendered"><div class="prompt input_prompt">
</div><div class="inner_cell">
<div class="text_cell_render border-box-sizing rendered_html">
<h1 id="Computing-Aggregates">Computing Aggregates<a class="anchor-link" href="#Computing-Aggregates">¶</a></h1>
</div>
</div>
</div>
<div class="cell border-box-sizing code_cell rendered">
<div class="input">
<div class="prompt input_prompt">In [46]:</div>
<div class="inner_cell">
    <div class="input_area">
<div class=" highlight hl-ipython3"><pre><span></span><span class="kn">from</span> <span class="nn">dateutil.parser</span> <span class="kn">import</span> <span class="n">parse</span>

<span class="n">prices_columns</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="p">{}</span>

<span class="k">for</span> <span class="n">k</span><span class="p">,</span><span class="n">v</span> <span class="ow">in</span> <span class="n">prices</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">items</span><span class="p">():</span>
    <span class="n">price</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">v</span>
    <span class="n">headers</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">price</span><span class="p">[</span><span class="mi">0</span><span class="p">]</span>
    <span class="n">price_columns</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="p">{}</span>
    <span class="k">for</span> <span class="n">i</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">header</span> <span class="ow">in</span> <span class="nb">enumerate</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">headers</span><span class="p">):</span>
        <span class="n">values</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="p">[</span><span class="n">p</span><span class="p">[</span><span class="n">i</span><span class="p">]</span> <span class="k">for</span> <span class="n">p</span> <span class="ow">in</span> <span class="n">price</span><span class="p">[</span><span class="mi">1</span><span class="p">:]]</span>
        <span class="k">if</span> <span class="n">i</span> <span class="o">></span> <span class="mi">0</span><span class="p">:</span>
            <span class="n">values</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="p">[</span><span class="nb">float</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">v</span><span class="p">)</span> <span class="k">for</span> <span class="n">v</span> <span class="ow">in</span> <span class="n">values</span><span class="p">]</span>
        <span class="k">else</span><span class="p">:</span>
            <span class="n">values</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="p">[</span><span class="n">parse</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">v</span><span class="p">)</span> <span class="k">for</span> <span class="n">v</span> <span class="ow">in</span> <span class="n">values</span><span class="p">]</span>
        <span class="n">price_columns</span><span class="p">[</span><span class="n">header</span><span class="p">]</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">values</span>
    <span class="n">prices_columns</span><span class="p">[</span><span class="n">k</span><span class="p">]</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">price_columns</span>
</pre></div>

    </div>
</div>
</div>

</div>
<div class="cell border-box-sizing code_cell rendered">
<div class="input">
<div class="prompt input_prompt">In [47]:</div>
<div class="inner_cell">

<div class=" highlight hl-ipython3"><pre><span></span><span class="kn">from</span> <span class="nn">statistics</span> <span class="kn">import</span> <span class="n">mean</span>

<span class="n">average_closing</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="p">{}</span>
<span class="k">for</span> <span class="n">k</span><span class="p">,</span><span class="n">v</span> <span class="ow">in</span> <span class="n">prices_columns</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">items</span><span class="p">():</span>
    <span class="n">average_closing</span><span class="p">[</span><span class="n">k</span><span class="p">]</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">mean</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">v</span><span class="p">[</span><span class="s2">"close"</span><span class="p">])</span>
</pre></div>

<span class="nb">sorted</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">closing_tuples</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">key</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="k">lambda</span> <span class="n">x</span><span class="p">:</span><span class="n">x</span><span class="p">[</span><span class="mi">1</span><span class="p">])</span>

<h1 id="Finding-The-Most-Traded-Stock-Each-Day">Finding The Most Traded Stock Each Day<a class="anchor-link" href="#Finding-The-Most-Traded-Stock-Each-Day">¶</a></h1>
</div>
</div>
</div>
<div class="cell border-box-sizing code_cell rendered">
<div class="input">
<div class="prompt input_prompt">In [49]:</div>
<div class="inner_cell">
    <div class="input_area">
<div class=" highlight hl-ipython3"><pre><span></span><span class="n">trades</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="p">{}</span>
<span class="k">for</span> <span class="n">k</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">v</span> <span class="ow">in</span> <span class="n">prices_columns</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">items</span><span class="p">():</span>
    <span class="k">for</span> <span class="n">i</span><span class="p">,</span><span class="n">date</span> <span class="ow">in</span> <span class="nb">enumerate</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">v</span><span class="p">[</span><span class="s2">"date"</span><span class="p">]):</span>
        <span class="k">if</span> <span class="n">date</span> <span class="ow">not</span> <span class="ow">in</span> <span class="n">trades</span><span class="p">:</span>
            <span class="n">trades</span><span class="p">[</span><span class="n">date</span><span class="p">]</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="p">[]</span>
        <span class="n">trades</span><span class="p">[</span><span class="n">date</span><span class="p">]</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">append</span><span class="p">([</span><span class="n">k</span><span class="p">,</span><span class="n">v</span><span class="p">[</span><span class="s2">"volume"</span><span class="p">][</span><span class="n">i</span><span class="p">]])</span>
</pre></div>

<div class=" highlight hl-ipython3"><pre><span></span><span class="n">most_traded</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="p">[]</span>
<span class="k">for</span> <span class="n">k</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">v</span> <span class="ow">in</span> <span class="n">trades</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">items</span><span class="p">():</span>
    <span class="n">ordered</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="nb">sorted</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">v</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">key</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="k">lambda</span> <span class="n">x</span><span class="p">:</span> <span class="n">x</span><span class="p">[</span><span class="mi">1</span><span class="p">])</span>
    <span class="n">symbol</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">ordered</span><span class="p">[</span><span class="o">-</span><span class="mi">1</span><span class="p">][</span><span class="mi">0</span><span class="p">]</span>
    <span class="n">most_traded</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">append</span><span class="p">([</span><span class="n">k</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">symbol</span><span class="p">])</span>
<span class="n">most_traded</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="nb">sorted</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">most_traded</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">key</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="k">lambda</span> <span class="n">x</span><span class="p">:</span> <span class="n">x</span><span class="p">[</span><span class="mi">0</span><span class="p">])</span>

<div class="cell border-box-sizing code_cell rendered">

<div class="prompt input_prompt">In [51]:</div>
<div class="inner_cell">

<div class=" highlight hl-ipython3"><pre><span></span><span class="n">daily_volumes</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="p">{}</span>

<span class="n">most_traded</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="p">[]</span>
<span class="k">for</span> <span class="n">k</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">v</span> <span class="ow">in</span> <span class="n">trades</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">items</span><span class="p">():</span>
    <span class="n">volume</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="nb">sum</span><span class="p">([</span><span class="n">item</span><span class="p">[</span><span class="mi">1</span><span class="p">]</span> <span class="k">for</span> <span class="n">item</span> <span class="ow">in</span> <span class="n">v</span><span class="p">])</span>
    <span class="n">daily_volumes</span><span class="p">[</span><span class="n">k</span><span class="p">]</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">volume</span>
</pre></div>

<div class="cell border-box-sizing code_cell rendered">
<div class="input">
<div class="prompt input_prompt">In [52]:</div>
<div class="inner_cell">
    <div class="input_area">
<div class=" highlight hl-ipython3"><pre><span></span><span class="n">volume_tuples</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="p">[[</span><span class="n">k</span><span class="p">,</span><span class="n">v</span><span class="p">]</span> <span class="k">for</span> <span class="n">k</span><span class="p">,</span><span class="n">v</span> <span class="ow">in</span> <span class="n">daily_volumes</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">items</span><span class="p">()]</span>
<span class="n">volume_tuples</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="nb">sorted</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">volume_tuples</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">key</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="k">lambda</span> <span class="n">x</span><span class="p">:</span> <span class="n">x</span><span class="p">[</span><span class="mi">1</span><span class="p">])</span>

<div class="input">

<div class="inner_cell">

<div class=" highlight hl-ipython3"><pre><span></span><span class="kn">import</span> <span class="nn">math</span>

<span class="n">high_volume_days</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="p">[</span><span class="n">v</span><span class="p">[</span><span class="mi">0</span><span class="p">]</span> <span class="k">for</span> <span class="n">v</span> <span class="ow">in</span> <span class="n">volume_tuples</span><span class="p">[</span><span class="o">-</span><span class="mi">10</span><span class="p">:]]</span>

<span class="k">def</span> <span class="nf">binary_search</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">array</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">search</span><span class="p">):</span>
    <span class="n">m</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="mi">0</span>
    <span class="n">i</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="mi">0</span>
    <span class="n">z</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="nb">len</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">array</span><span class="p">)</span> <span class="o">-</span> <span class="mi">1</span>
    <span class="k">while</span> <span class="n">i</span><span class="o"><=</span> <span class="n">z</span><span class="p">:</span>
        <span class="n">m</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">math</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">floor</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">i</span> <span class="o">+</span> <span class="p">((</span><span class="n">z</span> <span class="o">-</span> <span class="n">i</span><span class="p">)</span> <span class="o">/</span> <span class="mi">2</span><span class="p">))</span>
        <span class="k">if</span> <span class="n">array</span><span class="p">[</span><span class="n">m</span><span class="p">]</span> <span class="o">==</span> <span class="n">search</span><span class="p">:</span>
            <span class="k">return</span> <span class="n">m</span>
        <span class="k">elif</span> <span class="n">array</span><span class="p">[</span><span class="n">m</span><span class="p">]</span> <span class="o"><</span> <span class="n">search</span><span class="p">:</span>
            <span class="n">i</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">m</span> <span class="o">+</span> <span class="mi">1</span>
        <span class="k">elif</span> <span class="n">array</span><span class="p">[</span><span class="n">m</span><span class="p">]</span> <span class="o">></span> <span class="n">search</span><span class="p">:</span>
            <span class="n">z</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">m</span> <span class="o">-</span> <span class="mi">1</span>

<span class="n">high_volume_transactions</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="p">{}</span>
<span class="k">for</span> <span class="n">k</span><span class="p">,</span><span class="n">v</span> <span class="ow">in</span> <span class="n">prices_columns</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">items</span><span class="p">():</span>
    <span class="k">for</span> <span class="n">day</span> <span class="ow">in</span> <span class="n">high_volume_days</span><span class="p">:</span>
        <span class="n">ind</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">binary_search</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">v</span><span class="p">[</span><span class="s2">"date"</span><span class="p">],</span> <span class="n">day</span><span class="p">)</span>
        <span class="k">if</span> <span class="n">ind</span> <span class="ow">is</span> <span class="kc">None</span><span class="p">:</span>
            <span class="k">continue</span>
        <span class="k">if</span> <span class="n">k</span> <span class="ow">not</span> <span class="ow">in</span> <span class="n">high_volume_transactions</span><span class="p">:</span>
            <span class="n">high_volume_transactions</span><span class="p">[</span><span class="n">k</span><span class="p">]</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="p">[]</span>
        <span class="n">high_volume_transactions</span><span class="p">[</span><span class="n">k</span><span class="p">]</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">append</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">prices</span><span class="p">[</span><span class="n">k</span><span class="p">][</span><span class="n">ind</span><span class="p">])</span>
</pre></div>

<div class=" highlight hl-ipython3"><pre><span></span><span class="n">profits</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="p">[]</span>
<span class="k">for</span> <span class="n">k</span><span class="p">,</span><span class="n">v</span> <span class="ow">in</span> <span class="n">prices_columns</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">items</span><span class="p">():</span>
    <span class="n">percentage</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="p">(</span><span class="n">v</span><span class="p">[</span><span class="s2">"close"</span><span class="p">][</span><span class="o">-</span><span class="mi">1</span><span class="p">]</span> <span class="o">-</span> <span class="n">v</span><span class="p">[</span><span class="s2">"close"</span><span class="p">][</span><span class="mi">0</span><span class="p">])</span> <span class="o">/</span> <span class="n">v</span><span class="p">[</span><span class="s2">"close"</span><span class="p">][</span><span class="mi">0</span><span class="p">]</span>
    <span class="n">profits</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">append</span><span class="p">([</span><span class="n">k</span><span class="p">,</span><span class="n">percentage</span> <span class="o">*</span> <span class="mi">100</span><span class="p">])</span>

<span class="n">profits</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="nb">sorted</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">profits</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">key</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="k">lambda</span> <span class="n">x</span><span class="p">:</span> <span class="n">x</span><span class="p">[</span><span class="mi">1</span><span class="p">])</span>

<span class="n">profits</span><span class="p">[</span><span class="o">-</span><span class="mi">10</span><span class="p">:]</span>
</pre></div>

/* The following gets added to the <head> if it is detected that the user has a
 * monospace font with inconsistent normal/bold/italic height.  See
 * notebookmain.js.  Such fonts will have keywords vertically offset with
 * respect to the rest of the text.  The user should select a better font.
 * See: https://github.com/ipython/ipython/issues/1503
 *
 * .CodeMirror span {
 *      vertical-align: bottom;
 * }
 */
.CodeMirror {
  line-height: 1.21429em;
  /* Changed from 1em to our global default */
  font-size: 14px;
  height: auto;
  /* Changed to auto to autogrow */
  background: none;

}
.CodeMirror-scroll {
  /*  The CodeMirror docs are a bit fuzzy on if overflow-y should be hidden or visible.*/
  /*  We have found that if it is visible, vertical scrollbars appear with font size changes.*/
  overflow-y: hidden;
  overflow-x: auto;
}
.CodeMirror-lines {
  /* In CM2, this used to be 0.4em, but in CM3 it went to 4px. We need the em value because */
  /* we have set a different line-height and want this to scale with that. */
  /* Note that this should set vertical padding only, since CodeMirror assumes
       that horizontal padding will be set on CodeMirror pre */
  padding: 0.4em 0;
}

  padding: 0 8px 0 4px;
}
.CodeMirror-gutters {
  border-bottom-left-radius: 2px;
  border-top-left-radius: 2px;
}
.CodeMirror pre {
  /* In CM3 this went to 4px from 0 in CM2. This sets horizontal padding only,
    use .CodeMirror-lines for vertical */
  padding: 0 0.4em;
  border: 0;

<div class=" highlight hl-ipython3"><pre><span></span><span class="k">def</span> <span class="nf">extract_age</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">age_str</span><span class="p">):</span>

        <span class="k">return</span> <span class="kc">None</span>

/* The following gets added to the <head> if it is detected that the user has a
 * monospace font with inconsistent normal/bold/italic height.  See

 *      vertical-align: bottom;
 * }

.CodeMirror {
  line-height: 1.21429em;
  /* Changed from 1em to our global default */

  /* In CM2, this used to be 0.4em, but in CM3 it went to 4px. We need the em value because */

  /* Note that this should set vertical padding only, since CodeMirror assumes
       that horizontal padding will be set on CodeMirror pre */
  padding: 0.4em 0;

			<h1 id="firstHeading" class="firstHeading" lang="en">Cecil Peak</h1>
									<div id="bodyContent" class="mw-body-content">
									<div id="siteSub">From Wikipedia, the free encyclopedia</div>
								<div id="contentSub"></div>
												<div id="jump-to-nav" class="mw-jump">
					Jump to:					<a href="#mw-head">navigation</a>, 					<a href="#p-search">search</a>
				</div>
				<div id="mw-content-text" lang="en" dir="ltr" class="mw-content-ltr"><p><b>Cecil Peak</b> is a mountain in the <a href="/wiki/Wakatipu_Basin" title="Wakatipu Basin">Wakatipu Basin</a>, <a href="/wiki/New_Zealand" title="New Zealand">New Zealand</a> and reaches a height of 1,978 metres.<sup id="cite_ref-1" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-1">[1]</a></sup> It is on the south side of <a href="/wiki/Lake_Wakatipu" title="Lake Wakatipu">Lake Wakatipu</a>, south south-west of <a href="/wiki/Queenstown,_New_Zealand" title="Queenstown, New Zealand">Queenstown</a> and is highly prominent from around this area. <sup id="cite_ref-2" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-2">[2]</a></sup></p>
<div class="thumb tright">
<div class="thumbinner" style="width:502px;"><a href="/wiki/File:Cecil-Peak-and-Walter-Peak-with-snow.jpg" class="image"><img alt="" src="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/9/97/Cecil-Peak-and-Walter-Peak-with-snow.jpg/500px-Cecil-Peak-and-Walter-Peak-with-snow.jpg" width="500" height="158" class="thumbimage" srcset="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/9/97/Cecil-Peak-and-Walter-Peak-with-snow.jpg/750px-Cecil-Peak-and-Walter-Peak-with-snow.jpg 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/9/97/Cecil-Peak-and-Walter-Peak-with-snow.jpg/1000px-Cecil-Peak-and-Walter-Peak-with-snow.jpg 2x" data-file-width="3608" data-file-height="1143" /></a>
<div class="thumbcaption">
<div class="magnify"><a href="/wiki/File:Cecil-Peak-and-Walter-Peak-with-snow.jpg" class="internal" title="Enlarge"></a></div>
View from Fernhill of Cecil Peak (<a href="/wiki/Walter_Peak,_New_Zealand" class="mw-redirect" title="Walter Peak, New Zealand">Walter Peak</a> on right). Kā Kamu-a-Hakitekura is the <a href="/wiki/M%C4%81ori_language" title="Māori language">Māori</a> name for both mountains.</div>
</div>
</div>
<p>Vegetation is mainly grass and tussock (as it is under a pastoral lease<sup id="cite_ref-3" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-3">[3]</a></sup>) with trees near the waterline. <a href="/wiki/Hidden_Island,_New_Zealand" class="mw-redirect" title="Hidden Island, New Zealand">Hidden Island</a> is one of four islands in Lake Wakatipu and sits very close to the shoreline of Cecil Peak. On 27 March 2010 a local band performed an outdoor concert in a natural amphitheatre on the peak playing songs from the band <a href="/wiki/Pink_Floyd" title="Pink Floyd">Pink Floyd</a>.<sup id="cite_ref-4" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-4">[4]</a></sup></p>
<h2><span class="mw-headline" id="Name">Name</span><span class="mw-editsection"><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">[</span><a href="/w/index.php?title=Cecil_Peak&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1" title="Edit section: Name">edit</a><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></span></h2>
<p>Both Cecil Peak and the nearby mountain of Walter Peak were named after <a href="/wiki/William_Gilbert_Rees" title="William Gilbert Rees">William Rees'</a> eldest sons' first given names by the surveyor <a href="/wiki/James_McKerrow" title="James McKerrow">James McKerrow</a> in 1862.<sup id="cite_ref-5" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-5">[5]</a></sup></p>

<div class="cell border-box-sizing text_cell rendered"><div class="prompt input_prompt">
</div><div class="inner_cell">
<div class="text_cell_render border-box-sizing rendered_html">
<p>It appears that the main content is nested inside the <code>div</code> tag with the id <code>content</code>.</p>

</div>
</div>
</div>
<div class="cell border-box-sizing text_cell rendered"><div class="prompt input_prompt">
</div><div class="inner_cell">
<div class="text_cell_render border-box-sizing rendered_html">
<h1 id="Reading-In-The-Data">Reading In The Data<a class="anchor-link" href="#Reading-In-The-Data">¶</a></h1>
</div>
</div>
</div>
<div class="cell border-box-sizing code_cell rendered">
<div class="input">
<div class="prompt input_prompt">In [12]:</div>
<div class="inner_cell">
    <div class="input_area">
<div class=" highlight hl-ipython3"><pre><span></span><span class="kn">import</span> <span class="nn">concurrent.futures</span>
<span class="kn">import</span> <span class="nn">time</span>

<span class="n">pool</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">concurrent</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">futures</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">ThreadPoolExecutor</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">max_workers</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="mi">4</span><span class="p">)</span>

<span class="k">def</span> <span class="nf">read_data</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">filename</span><span class="p">):</span>
    <span class="k">with</span> <span class="nb">open</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">filename</span><span class="p">)</span> <span class="k">as</span> <span class="n">f</span><span class="p">:</span>
        <span class="n">data</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">f</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">read</span><span class="p">()</span>
    <span class="k">return</span> <span class="n">data</span>

<span class="n">start</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">time</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">time</span><span class="p">()</span>
<span class="n">filenames</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="p">[</span><span class="s2">"wiki/</span><span class="si">{}</span><span class="s2">"</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">format</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">f</span><span class="p">)</span> <span class="k">for</span> <span class="n">f</span> <span class="ow">in</span> <span class="n">os</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">listdir</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="s2">"wiki"</span><span class="p">)]</span>
<span class="n">content</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">pool</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">map</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">read_data</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">filenames</span><span class="p">)</span>
<span class="n">content</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="nb">list</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">content</span><span class="p">)</span>

<span class="n">end</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">time</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">time</span><span class="p">()</span>
<span class="nb">print</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">end</span> <span class="o">-</span> <span class="n">start</span><span class="p">)</span>
<span class="n">articles</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="p">[</span><span class="n">f</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">replace</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="s2">".html"</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="s2">""</span><span class="p">)</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">replace</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="s2">"wiki/"</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="s2">""</span><span class="p">)</span> <span class="k">for</span> <span class="n">f</span> <span class="ow">in</span> <span class="n">filenames</span><span class="p">]</span>
</pre></div>

    </div>
</div>
</div>

<div class="cell border-box-sizing text_cell rendered"><div class="prompt input_prompt">
</div><div class="inner_cell">
<div class="text_cell_render border-box-sizing rendered_html">
<p>After doing some profiling, it doesn't appear that threading makes a huge difference to performance.  It may be because although files are opened, most of the task is offset by the overhead of creating new threads.</p>

</div>
</div>
</div>
<div class="cell border-box-sizing text_cell rendered"><div class="prompt input_prompt">
</div><div class="inner_cell">
<div class="text_cell_render border-box-sizing rendered_html">
<h1 id="Remove-Extraneous-Markup">Remove Extraneous Markup<a class="anchor-link" href="#Remove-Extraneous-Markup">¶</a></h1>
</div>
</div>
</div>
<div class="cell border-box-sizing code_cell rendered">
<div class="input">
<div class="prompt input_prompt">In [26]:</div>
<div class="inner_cell">
    <div class="input_area">
<div class=" highlight hl-ipython3"><pre><span></span><span class="kn">from</span> <span class="nn">bs4</span> <span class="kn">import</span> <span class="n">BeautifulSoup</span>

<span class="k">def</span> <span class="nf">parse_html</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">html</span><span class="p">):</span>
    <span class="n">soup</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">BeautifulSoup</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">html</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="s1">'html.parser'</span><span class="p">)</span>
    <span class="k">return</span> <span class="nb">str</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">soup</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">find_all</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="s2">"div"</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="nb">id</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="s2">"content"</span><span class="p">)[</span><span class="mi">0</span><span class="p">])</span>

<span class="n">start</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">time</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">time</span><span class="p">()</span>
<span class="n">pool</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">concurrent</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">futures</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">ProcessPoolExecutor</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">max_workers</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="mi">3</span><span class="p">)</span>
<span class="n">parsed</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">pool</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">map</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">parse_html</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">content</span><span class="p">)</span>
<span class="n">parsed</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="nb">list</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">parsed</span><span class="p">)</span>
<span class="n">end</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">time</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">time</span><span class="p">()</span>

<span class="nb">print</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">end</span> <span class="o">-</span> <span class="n">start</span><span class="p">)</span>
</pre></div>

    </div>
</div>

<div class="cell border-box-sizing code_cell rendered">
