<div class="text_cell_render border-box-sizing rendered_html">
<h1 id="Grouped-bar-plots,-part-2">Grouped bar plots, part 2<a class="anchor-link" href="#Grouped-bar-plots,-part-2">¶</a></h1>
</div>
</div>
</div>
<div class="cell border-box-sizing code_cell rendered">
<div class="input">
<div class="prompt input_prompt">In [126]:</div>
<div class="inner_cell">
    <div class="input_area">
<div class=" highlight hl-ipython3"><pre><span></span><span class="c1">## Part 1</span>

<span class="kn">import</span> <span class="nn">numpy</span> <span class="k">as</span> <span class="nn">np</span>
<span class="n">recent_grads</span><span class="p">[</span><span class="s2">"ShareMen"</span><span class="p">]</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">recent_grads</span><span class="p">[</span><span class="s2">"Men"</span><span class="p">]</span> <span class="o">/</span> <span class="n">recent_grads</span><span class="p">[</span><span class="s2">"Total"</span><span class="p">]</span>

<span class="n">fig_rg2</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">plt</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">figure</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">figsize</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="mi">6</span><span class="p">,</span><span class="mi">5</span><span class="p">))</span>
<span class="n">ax1_rg2</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">fig_rg2</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">add_subplot</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="mi">1</span><span class="p">,</span><span class="mi">1</span><span class="p">,</span><span class="mi">1</span><span class="p">)</span>

<span class="n">arts</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">recent_grads</span><span class="p">[</span><span class="n">recent_grads</span><span class="p">[</span><span class="s2">"Major_category"</span><span class="p">]</span> <span class="o">==</span> <span class="s2">"Arts"</span><span class="p">]</span>
<span class="n">major_names</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">arts</span><span class="p">[</span><span class="s2">"Major"</span><span class="p">]</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">tolist</span><span class="p">()</span>
<span class="n">locs</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">np</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">arange</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="nb">len</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">major_names</span><span class="p">))</span>
<span class="n">width</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="mf">0.35</span>

<span class="c1"># List representation of these columns</span>
<span class="n">men_proportions</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">arts</span><span class="p">[</span><span class="s2">"ShareMen"</span><span class="p">]</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">tolist</span><span class="p">()</span>
<span class="n">women_proportions</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">arts</span><span class="p">[</span><span class="s2">"ShareWomen"</span><span class="p">]</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">tolist</span><span class="p">()</span>

<span class="c1"># Generate both the bars</span>
<span class="n">bar_1</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">ax1_rg2</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">bar</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">locs</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">men_proportions</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">width</span><span class="p">)</span>
<span class="n">ax1_rg2</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">set_xticklabels</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">major_names</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">rotation</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="mi">90</span><span class="p">)</span>

<span class="c1">## Part 2</span>

<span class="c1"># Each value offset by `0.35`</span>
<span class="n">offset_locs</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">locs</span> <span class="o">+</span> <span class="n">width</span>

<span class="c1"># Set of bars for `ShareWomen`</span>
<span class="n">bar_2</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">ax1_rg2</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">bar</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">offset_locs</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">women_proportions</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">width</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">color</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="s2">"green"</span><span class="p">)</span>

<span class="c1"># Align x labels with bars better</span>
<span class="n">ax1_rg2</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">set_xticks</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">offset_locs</span><span class="p">)</span>

<span class="c1"># Create a legend</span>
<span class="n">plt</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">legend</span><span class="p">((</span><span class="n">bar_1</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">bar_2</span><span class="p">),</span> <span class="p">(</span><span class="s2">"ShareMen"</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="s2">"ShareWomen"</span><span class="p">),</span> <span class="n">loc</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="s2">"upper left"</span><span class="p">)</span>

<span class="c1"># Display the background grid</span>
<span class="n">plt</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">grid</span><span class="p">()</span>
<span class="n">plt</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">show</span><span class="p">()</span>
</pre></div>

    </div>

<div class="cell border-box-sizing text_cell rendered"><div class="prompt input_prompt">
</div><div class="inner_cell">
<div class="text_cell_render border-box-sizing rendered_html">
<p>It looks like the game log has a record of over 170,000 games.  It looks like these games are chronologically ordered and occur between 1871 and 2016.</p>
<p>For each game we have:</p>
<ul>
<li>general information on the game</li>
<li>team level stats for each team</li>
<li>a list of players from each team, numbered, with their defensive positions</li>
<li>the umpires that officiated the game</li>
<li>some 'awards', like winning and losing pitcher</li>
</ul>
<p>We have a <code>game_log_fields.txt</code> file that tell us that the player number corresponds with the order in which they batted.</p>
<p>It's worth noting that there is no natural primary key column for this table.</p>

</div>
</div>
</div>

<div class="text_cell_render border-box-sizing rendered_html">

<p>It also looks like coaches and managers are two different things in baseball.  After some research, managers are what would be called a 'coach' or 'head coach' in other sports, and coaches are more specialized, like base coaches.  It also seems like coaches aren't recorded in the game log.</p>

</div><div class="inner_cell">
<div class="text_cell_render border-box-sizing rendered_html">
<p>It appears that teams move between leagues and cities.  The team_id changes when this happens, <code>franch_id</code> (which is probably 'Franchise') helps us tie all of this together.</p>

</div>
</div>
</div>
<div class="cell border-box-sizing text_cell rendered"><div class="prompt input_prompt">
</div><div class="inner_cell">
<div class="text_cell_render border-box-sizing rendered_html">
<p><strong>Defensive Positions</strong></p>
<p>In the game log, each player has a defensive position listed, which seems to be a number between 1-10.  Doing some research around this, I found <a href="http://probaseballinsider.com/baseball-instruction/baseball-basics/baseball-basics-positions/">this article</a> which gives us a list of names for each numbered position:</p>
<ol>
<li>Pitcher</li>
<li>Catcher</li>
<li>1st Base</li>
<li>2nd Base</li>
<li>3rd Base</li>
<li>Shortstop</li>
<li>Left Field</li>
<li>Center Field</li>
<li>Right Field</li>
</ol>
<p>The 10th position isn't included, it may be a way of describing a designated hitter that does not field.  I can find a retrosheet page that indicates that position <code>0</code> is used for this, but we don't have any position 0 in our data.  I have chosen to make this an 'Unknown Position' so I'm not including data based on a hunch.</p>
<p><strong>Leagues</strong></p>
<p>Wikipedia tells us there are currently two leagues - the American (AL) and National (NL). Let's start by finding out what leagues are listed in the main game log:</p>

</div>
</div>
</div>
<div class="cell border-box-sizing code_cell rendered">
<div class="input">
<div class="prompt input_prompt">In [9]:</div>
<div class="inner_cell">
    <div class="input_area">
<div class=" highlight hl-ipython3"><pre><span></span><span class="n">log</span><span class="p">[</span><span class="s2">"h_league"</span><span class="p">]</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">value_counts</span><span class="p">()</span>
</pre></div>

    </div>
</div>
</div>

<div class="output_wrapper">
<div class="output">


<div class="output_area">

    <div class="prompt output_prompt">Out[9]:</div>




<div class="output_text output_subarea output_execute_result">
<pre>NL    88867
AL    74712
AA     5039
FL     1243
PL      532
UA      428
Name: h_league, dtype: int64</pre>
</div>

</div>

</div>
</div>

</div>
<div class="cell border-box-sizing text_cell rendered"><div class="prompt input_prompt">
</div><div class="inner_cell">
<div class="text_cell_render border-box-sizing rendered_html">
<p>It looks like most of our games fall into the two current leagues, but that there are four other leagues.  Let's write a quick function to get some info on the years of these leagues:</p>

</div>
</div>
</div>
<div class="cell border-box-sizing code_cell rendered">
<div class="input">
<div class="prompt input_prompt">In [10]:</div>
<div class="inner_cell">
    <div class="input_area">
<div class=" highlight hl-ipython3"><pre><span></span><span class="k">def</span> <span class="nf">league_info</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">league</span><span class="p">):</span>
    <span class="n">league_games</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">log</span><span class="p">[</span><span class="n">log</span><span class="p">[</span><span class="s2">"h_league"</span><span class="p">]</span> <span class="o">==</span> <span class="n">league</span><span class="p">]</span>
    <span class="n">earliest</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">league_games</span><span class="p">[</span><span class="s2">"date"</span><span class="p">]</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">min</span><span class="p">()</span>
    <span class="n">latest</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">league_games</span><span class="p">[</span><span class="s2">"date"</span><span class="p">]</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">max</span><span class="p">()</span>
    <span class="nb">print</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="s2">"</span><span class="si">{}</span><span class="s2"> went from </span><span class="si">{}</span><span class="s2"> to </span><span class="si">{}</span><span class="s2">"</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">format</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">league</span><span class="p">,</span><span class="n">earliest</span><span class="p">,</span><span class="n">latest</span><span class="p">))</span>

<span class="k">for</span> <span class="n">league</span> <span class="ow">in</span> <span class="n">log</span><span class="p">[</span><span class="s2">"h_league"</span><span class="p">]</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">unique</span><span class="p">():</span>
    <span class="n">league_info</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">league</span><span class="p">)</span>
</pre></div>

    </div>
</div>
</div>

<div class="cell border-box-sizing text_cell rendered"><div class="prompt input_prompt">
</div><div class="inner_cell">
<div class="text_cell_render border-box-sizing rendered_html">
<p>Now we have some years which will help us do some research.  After some googling we come up with:</p>
<ul>
<li><code>NL</code>: National League</li>
<li><code>AL</code>: American League</li>
<li><code>AA</code>: <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/American_Association_%2819th_century%29">American Association</a></li>
<li><code>FL</code>: <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Federal_League">Federal League</a></li>
<li><code>PL</code>: <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Players%27_League">Players League</a></li>
<li><code>UA</code>: <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Union_Association">Union Association</a></li>
</ul>
<p>It also looks like we have about 1000 games where the home team doesn't have a value for league.</p>

</div>
</div>
</div>
<div class="cell border-box-sizing text_cell rendered"><div class="prompt input_prompt">
</div><div class="inner_cell">
<div class="text_cell_render border-box-sizing rendered_html">
<h2 id="Importing-Data-into-SQLite">Importing Data into SQLite<a class="anchor-link" href="#Importing-Data-into-SQLite">¶</a></h2>
</div>
</div>
</div>
<div class="cell border-box-sizing code_cell rendered">
<div class="input">
<div class="prompt input_prompt">In [11]:</div>
<div class="inner_cell">
    <div class="input_area">
<div class=" highlight hl-ipython3"><pre><span></span><span class="c1"># These helper functions will be useful as we work</span>
<span class="c1"># with the SQLite database from python</span>

<span class="n">DB</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="s2">"mlb.db"</span>

<span class="k">def</span> <span class="nf">run_query</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">q</span><span class="p">):</span>
    <span class="k">with</span> <span class="n">sqlite3</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">connect</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">DB</span><span class="p">)</span> <span class="k">as</span> <span class="n">conn</span><span class="p">:</span>
        <span class="k">return</span> <span class="n">pd</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">read_sql</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">q</span><span class="p">,</span><span class="n">conn</span><span class="p">)</span>

<span class="k">def</span> <span class="nf">run_command</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">c</span><span class="p">):</span>
    <span class="k">with</span> <span class="n">sqlite3</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">connect</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">DB</span><span class="p">)</span> <span class="k">as</span> <span class="n">conn</span><span class="p">:</span>
        <span class="n">conn</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">execute</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="s1">'PRAGMA foreign_keys = ON;'</span><span class="p">)</span>
        <span class="n">conn</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">isolation_level</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="kc">None</span>
        <span class="n">conn</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">execute</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">c</span><span class="p">)</span>

<span class="k">def</span> <span class="nf">show_tables</span><span class="p">():</span>
    <span class="n">q</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="s1">'''</span>
<span class="s1">    SELECT</span>
<span class="s1">        name,</span>
<span class="s1">        type</span>
<span class="s1">    FROM sqlite_master</span>
<span class="s1">    WHERE type IN ("table","view");</span>
<span class="s1">    '''</span>
    <span class="k">return</span> <span class="n">run_query</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">q</span><span class="p">)</span>
</pre></div>

    </div>
</div>
</div>

</div>
<div class="cell border-box-sizing code_cell rendered">
<div class="input">
<div class="prompt input_prompt">In [12]:</div>
<div class="inner_cell">
    <div class="input_area">
<div class=" highlight hl-ipython3"><pre><span></span><span class="n">tables</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="p">{</span>
    <span class="s2">"game_log"</span><span class="p">:</span> <span class="n">log</span><span class="p">,</span>
    <span class="s2">"person_codes"</span><span class="p">:</span> <span class="n">person</span><span class="p">,</span>
    <span class="s2">"team_codes"</span><span class="p">:</span> <span class="n">team</span><span class="p">,</span>
    <span class="s2">"park_codes"</span><span class="p">:</span> <span class="n">park</span>
<span class="p">}</span>

<span class="k">with</span> <span class="n">sqlite3</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">connect</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">DB</span><span class="p">)</span> <span class="k">as</span> <span class="n">conn</span><span class="p">:</span>    
    <span class="k">for</span> <span class="n">name</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">data</span> <span class="ow">in</span> <span class="n">tables</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">items</span><span class="p">():</span>
        <span class="n">conn</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">execute</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="s2">"DROP TABLE IF EXISTS </span><span class="si">{}</span><span class="s2">;"</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">format</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">name</span><span class="p">))</span>

<div class="cell border-box-sizing text_cell rendered"><div class="prompt input_prompt">
</div><div class="inner_cell">
<div class="text_cell_render border-box-sizing rendered_html">
<h2 id="Looking-for-Normalization-Opportunities">Looking for Normalization Opportunities<a class="anchor-link" href="#Looking-for-Normalization-Opportunities">¶</a></h2>
</div>
</div>
</div>
<div class="cell border-box-sizing text_cell rendered"><div class="prompt input_prompt">
</div><div class="inner_cell">
<div class="text_cell_render border-box-sizing rendered_html">
<p>The following are opportunities for normalization of our data:</p>
<ul>
<li>In <code>person_codes</code>, all the debut dates will be able to be reproduced using game log data.</li>
<li>In <code>team_codes</code>, the start, end and sequence columns will be able to be reproduced using game log data.</li>
<li>In <code>park_codes</code>, the start and end years will be able to be reproduced using game log data.  While technically the state is an attribute of the city, we might not want to have a an incomplete city/state table so we will leave this in.</li>
<li>There are lots of places in <code>game</code> log where we have a player ID followed by the players name.  We will be able to remove this and use the name data in <code>person_codes</code></li>
<li>In <code>game_log</code>, all offensive and defensive stats are repeated for the home team and the visiting team.  We could break these out and have a table that lists each game twice, one for each team, and cut out this column repetition.</li>
<li>Similarly, in <code>game_log</code>, we have a listing for 9 players on each team with their positions - we can remove these and have one table that tracks player appearances and their positions.</li>
<li>We can do a similar thing with the umpires from <code>game_log</code>, instead of listing all four positions as columns, we can put the umpires either in their own table or make one table for players, umpires and managers.</li>
<li>We have several awards in <code>game_log</code> like winning pitcher and losing pitcher.  We can either break these out into their own table, have a table for awards, or combine the awards in with general appearances like the players and umpires.</li>
</ul>

</div>
</div>
</div>
<div class="cell border-box-sizing text_cell rendered"><div class="prompt input_prompt">

<div class="cell border-box-sizing text_cell rendered"><div class="prompt input_prompt">
</div><div class="inner_cell">
<div class="text_cell_render border-box-sizing rendered_html">
<h2 id="Adding-the-Person-Appearance-Table">Adding the Person Appearance Table<a class="anchor-link" href="#Adding-the-Person-Appearance-Table">¶</a></h2>
</div>
</div>
</div>
<div class="cell border-box-sizing code_cell rendered">
<div class="input">
<div class="prompt input_prompt">In [22]:</div>
<div class="inner_cell">
    <div class="input_area">
<div class=" highlight hl-ipython3"><pre><span></span><span class="n">c0</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="s2">"DROP TABLE IF EXISTS person_appearance"</span>

<span class="n">run_command</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">c0</span><span class="p">)</span>

<span class="n">c1</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="s2">"""</span>
<span class="s2">CREATE TABLE person_appearance (</span>
<span class="s2">    appearance_id INTEGER PRIMARY KEY,</span>
<span class="s2">    person_id TEXT,</span>
<span class="s2">    team_id TEXT,</span>
<span class="s2">    game_id TEXT,</span>
<span class="s2">    appearance_type_id,</span>
<span class="s2">    FOREIGN KEY (person_id) REFERENCES person(person_id),</span>
<span class="s2">    FOREIGN KEY (team_id) REFERENCES team(team_id),</span>
<span class="s2">    FOREIGN KEY (game_id) REFERENCES game(game_id),</span>
<span class="s2">    FOREIGN KEY (appearance_type_id) REFERENCES appearance_type(appearance_type_id)</span>
<span class="s2">);</span>
<span class="s2">"""</span>

<span class="n">c2</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="s2">"""</span>
<span class="s2">INSERT OR IGNORE INTO person_appearance (</span>
<span class="s2">    game_id,</span>
<span class="s2">    team_id,</span>
<span class="s2">    person_id,</span>
<span class="s2">    appearance_type_id</span>
<span class="s2">) </span>
<span class="s2">    SELECT</span>
<span class="s2">        game_id,</span>
<span class="s2">        NULL,</span>
<span class="s2">        hp_umpire_id,</span>
<span class="s2">        "UHP"</span>
<span class="s2">    FROM game_log</span>
<span class="s2">    WHERE hp_umpire_id IS NOT NULL    </span>

<span class="s2">UNION</span>

<span class="s2">    SELECT</span>
<span class="s2">        game_id,</span>
<span class="s2">        NULL,</span>
<span class="s2">        [1b_umpire_id],</span>
<span class="s2">        "U1B"</span>
<span class="s2">    FROM game_log</span>
<span class="s2">    WHERE "1b_umpire_id" IS NOT NULL</span>

<span class="s2">UNION</span>

<span class="s2">    SELECT</span>
<span class="s2">        game_id,</span>
<span class="s2">        NULL,</span>
<span class="s2">        [2b_umpire_id],</span>
<span class="s2">        "U2B"</span>
<span class="s2">    FROM game_log</span>
<span class="s2">    WHERE [2b_umpire_id] IS NOT NULL</span>

<span class="s2">UNION</span>

<span class="s2">    SELECT</span>
<span class="s2">        game_id,</span>
<span class="s2">        NULL,</span>
<span class="s2">        [3b_umpire_id],</span>
<span class="s2">        "U3B"</span>
<span class="s2">    FROM game_log</span>
<span class="s2">    WHERE [3b_umpire_id] IS NOT NULL</span>

<span class="s2">UNION</span>

<span class="s2">    SELECT</span>
<span class="s2">        game_id,</span>
<span class="s2">        NULL,</span>
<span class="s2">        lf_umpire_id,</span>
<span class="s2">        "ULF"</span>
<span class="s2">    FROM game_log</span>
<span class="s2">    WHERE lf_umpire_id IS NOT NULL</span>

<span class="s2">UNION</span>

<span class="s2">    SELECT</span>
<span class="s2">        game_id,</span>
<span class="s2">        NULL,</span>
<span class="s2">        rf_umpire_id,</span>
<span class="s2">        "URF"</span>
<span class="s2">    FROM game_log</span>
<span class="s2">    WHERE rf_umpire_id IS NOT NULL</span>

<span class="s2">UNION</span>

<span class="s2">    SELECT</span>
<span class="s2">        game_id,</span>
<span class="s2">        v_name,</span>
<span class="s2">        v_manager_id,</span>
<span class="s2">        "MM"</span>
<span class="s2">    FROM game_log</span>
<span class="s2">    WHERE v_manager_id IS NOT NULL</span>

<span class="s2">UNION</span>

<span class="s2">    SELECT</span>
<span class="s2">        game_id,</span>
<span class="s2">        h_name,</span>
<span class="s2">        h_manager_id,</span>
<span class="s2">        "MM"</span>
<span class="s2">    FROM game_log</span>
<span class="s2">    WHERE h_manager_id IS NOT NULL</span>

<span class="s2">UNION</span>

<span class="s2">    SELECT</span>
<span class="s2">        game_id,</span>
<span class="s2">        CASE</span>
<span class="s2">            WHEN h_score > v_score THEN h_name</span>
<span class="s2">            ELSE v_name</span>
<span class="s2">            END,</span>
<span class="s2">        winning_pitcher_id,</span>
<span class="s2">        "AWP"</span>
<span class="s2">    FROM game_log</span>
<span class="s2">    WHERE winning_pitcher_id IS NOT NULL</span>

<span class="s2">UNION</span>

<span class="s2">    SELECT</span>
<span class="s2">        game_id,</span>
<span class="s2">        CASE</span>
<span class="s2">            WHEN h_score < v_score THEN h_name</span>
<span class="s2">            ELSE v_name</span>
<span class="s2">            END,</span>
<span class="s2">        losing_pitcher_id,</span>
<span class="s2">        "ALP"</span>
<span class="s2">    FROM game_log</span>
<span class="s2">    WHERE losing_pitcher_id IS NOT NULL</span>

<span class="s2">UNION</span>

<span class="s2">    SELECT</span>
<span class="s2">        game_id,</span>
<span class="s2">        CASE</span>
<span class="s2">            WHEN h_score > v_score THEN h_name</span>
<span class="s2">            ELSE v_name</span>
<span class="s2">            END,</span>
<span class="s2">        saving_pitcher_id,</span>
<span class="s2">        "ASP"</span>
<span class="s2">    FROM game_log</span>
<span class="s2">    WHERE saving_pitcher_id IS NOT NULL</span>

<span class="s2">UNION</span>

<span class="s2">    SELECT</span>
<span class="s2">        game_id,</span>
<span class="s2">        CASE</span>
<span class="s2">            WHEN h_score > v_score THEN h_name</span>
<span class="s2">            ELSE v_name</span>
<span class="s2">            END,</span>
<span class="s2">        winning_rbi_batter_id,</span>
<span class="s2">        "AWB"</span>
<span class="s2">    FROM game_log</span>
<span class="s2">    WHERE winning_rbi_batter_id IS NOT NULL</span>

<span class="s2">UNION</span>

<span class="s2">    SELECT</span>
<span class="s2">        game_id,</span>
<span class="s2">        v_name,</span>
<span class="s2">        v_starting_pitcher_id,</span>
<span class="s2">        "PSP"</span>
<span class="s2">    FROM game_log</span>
<span class="s2">    WHERE v_starting_pitcher_id IS NOT NULL</span>

<span class="s2">UNION</span>

<span class="s2">    SELECT</span>
<span class="s2">        game_id,</span>
<span class="s2">        h_name,</span>
<span class="s2">        h_starting_pitcher_id,</span>
<span class="s2">        "PSP"</span>
<span class="s2">    FROM game_log</span>
<span class="s2">    WHERE h_starting_pitcher_id IS NOT NULL;</span>
<span class="s2">"""</span>

<span class="n">template</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="s2">"""</span>
<span class="s2">INSERT INTO person_appearance (</span>
<span class="s2">    game_id,</span>
<span class="s2">    team_id,</span>
<span class="s2">    person_id,</span>
<span class="s2">    appearance_type_id</span>
<span class="s2">) </span>
<span class="s2">    SELECT</span>
<span class="s2">        game_id,</span>
<span class="s2">        </span><span class="si">{hv}</span><span class="s2">_name,</span>
<span class="s2">        </span><span class="si">{hv}</span><span class="s2">_player_</span><span class="si">{num}</span><span class="s2">_id,</span>
<span class="s2">        "O</span><span class="si">{num}</span><span class="s2">"</span>
<span class="s2">    FROM game_log</span>
<span class="s2">    WHERE </span><span class="si">{hv}</span><span class="s2">_player_</span><span class="si">{num}</span><span class="s2">_id IS NOT NULL</span>

<span class="s2">UNION</span>

<span class="s2">    SELECT</span>
<span class="s2">        game_id,</span>
<span class="s2">        </span><span class="si">{hv}</span><span class="s2">_name,</span>
<span class="s2">        </span><span class="si">{hv}</span><span class="s2">_player_</span><span class="si">{num}</span><span class="s2">_id,</span>
<span class="s2">        "D" || CAST(</span><span class="si">{hv}</span><span class="s2">_player_</span><span class="si">{num}</span><span class="s2">_def_pos AS INT)</span>
<span class="s2">    FROM game_log</span>
<span class="s2">    WHERE </span><span class="si">{hv}</span><span class="s2">_player_</span><span class="si">{num}</span><span class="s2">_id IS NOT NULL;</span>
<span class="s2">"""</span>

<span class="n">run_command</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">c1</span><span class="p">)</span>
<span class="n">run_command</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">c2</span><span class="p">)</span>

<span class="k">for</span> <span class="n">hv</span> <span class="ow">in</span> <span class="p">[</span><span class="s2">"h"</span><span class="p">,</span><span class="s2">"v"</span><span class="p">]:</span>
    <span class="k">for</span> <span class="n">num</span> <span class="ow">in</span> <span class="nb">range</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="mi">1</span><span class="p">,</span><span class="mi">10</span><span class="p">):</span>
        <span class="n">query_vars</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="p">{</span>
            <span class="s2">"hv"</span><span class="p">:</span> <span class="n">hv</span><span class="p">,</span>
            <span class="s2">"num"</span><span class="p">:</span> <span class="n">num</span>
        <span class="p">}</span>
        <span class="n">run_command</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">template</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">format</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="o">**</span><span class="n">query_vars</span><span class="p">))</span>
</pre></div>

<div class=" highlight hl-ipython3"><pre><span></span><span class="nb">print</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">run_query</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="s2">"SELECT COUNT(DISTINCT game_id) games_game FROM game"</span><span class="p">))</span>
<span class="nb">print</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">run_query</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="s2">"SELECT COUNT(DISTINCT game_id) games_person_appearance FROM person_appearance"</span><span class="p">))</span>

<span class="n">q</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="s2">"""</span>
<span class="s2">SELECT</span>
<span class="s2">    pa.*,</span>
<span class="s2">    at.name,</span>
<span class="s2">    at.category</span>
<span class="s2">FROM person_appearance pa</span>
<span class="s2">INNER JOIN appearance_type at on at.appearance_type_id = pa.appearance_type_id</span>
<span class="s2">WHERE PA.game_id = (</span>
<span class="s2">                   SELECT max(game_id)</span>
<span class="s2">                    FROM person_appearance</span>
<span class="s2">                   )</span>
<span class="s2">ORDER BY team_id, appearance_type_id</span>
<span class="s2">"""</span>

<span class="n">run_query</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">q</span><span class="p">)</span>
</pre></div>

<div class="cell border-box-sizing text_cell rendered"><div class="prompt input_prompt">
</div><div class="inner_cell">
<div class="text_cell_render border-box-sizing rendered_html">

</div>
</div>
</div>
<div class="cell border-box-sizing code_cell rendered">
<div class="input">
<div class="prompt input_prompt">In [30]:</div>
<div class="inner_cell">
    <div class="input_area">
<div class=" highlight hl-ipython3"><pre><span></span><span class="kn">import</span> <span class="nn">csv</span>

<span class="k">with</span> <span class="nb">open</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="s2">"guns.csv"</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="s2">"r"</span><span class="p">)</span> <span class="k">as</span> <span class="n">f</span><span class="p">:</span>
    <span class="n">reader</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">csv</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">reader</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">f</span><span class="p">)</span>
    <span class="n">data</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="nb">list</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">reader</span><span class="p">)</span>
</pre></div>

<div class=" highlight hl-ipython3"><pre><span></span><span class="nb">print</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">data</span><span class="p">[:</span><span class="mi">5</span><span class="p">])</span>
</pre></div>

<div class="inner_cell">
    <div class="input_area">
<div class=" highlight hl-ipython3"><pre><span></span><span class="n">years</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="p">[</span><span class="n">row</span><span class="p">[</span><span class="mi">1</span><span class="p">]</span> <span class="k">for</span> <span class="n">row</span> <span class="ow">in</span> <span class="n">data</span><span class="p">]</span>

<span class="n">year_counts</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="p">{}</span>
<span class="k">for</span> <span class="n">year</span> <span class="ow">in</span> <span class="n">years</span><span class="p">:</span>
    <span class="k">if</span> <span class="n">year</span> <span class="ow">not</span> <span class="ow">in</span> <span class="n">year_counts</span><span class="p">:</span>
        <span class="n">year_counts</span><span class="p">[</span><span class="n">year</span><span class="p">]</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="mi">1</span>
    <span class="k">else</span><span class="p">:</span>  
        <span class="n">year_counts</span><span class="p">[</span><span class="n">year</span><span class="p">]</span> <span class="o">+=</span> <span class="mi">1</span>

<span class="n">year_counts</span>

    <span class="n">sex_counts</span><span class="p">[</span><span class="n">sex</span><span class="p">]</span> <span class="o">+=</span> <span class="mi">1</span>
<span class="n">sex_counts</span>

<div class="cell border-box-sizing code_cell rendered">
<div class="input">
<div class="prompt input_prompt">In [36]:</div>
<div class="inner_cell">
    <div class="input_area">
<div class=" highlight hl-ipython3"><pre><span></span><span class="n">races</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="p">[</span><span class="n">row</span><span class="p">[</span><span class="mi">7</span><span class="p">]</span> <span class="k">for</span> <span class="n">row</span> <span class="ow">in</span> <span class="n">data</span><span class="p">]</span>
<span class="n">race_counts</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="p">{}</span>
<span class="k">for</span> <span class="n">race</span> <span class="ow">in</span> <span class="n">races</span><span class="p">:</span>
    <span class="k">if</span> <span class="n">race</span> <span class="ow">not</span> <span class="ow">in</span> <span class="n">race_counts</span><span class="p">:</span>
        <span class="n">race_counts</span><span class="p">[</span><span class="n">race</span><span class="p">]</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="mi">0</span>
    <span class="n">race_counts</span><span class="p">[</span><span class="n">race</span><span class="p">]</span> <span class="o">+=</span> <span class="mi">1</span>
<span class="n">race_counts</span>

<div class="cell border-box-sizing text_cell rendered"><div class="prompt input_prompt">
</div><div class="inner_cell">
<div class="text_cell_render border-box-sizing rendered_html">
<h2 id="Findings-so-far">Findings so far<a class="anchor-link" href="#Findings-so-far">¶</a></h2><p>Gun deaths in the US seem to disproportionately affect men vs women.  They also seem to disproportionately affect minorities, although having some data on the percentage of each race in the overall US population would help.</p>
<p>There appears to be a minor seasonal correlation, with gun deaths peaking in the summer and declining in the winter.  It might be useful to filter by intent, to see if different categories of intent have different correlations with season, race, or gender.</p>

</div>
</div>
</div>
<div class="cell border-box-sizing text_cell rendered"><div class="prompt input_prompt">
</div><div class="inner_cell">
<div class="text_cell_render border-box-sizing rendered_html">
<h1 id="Reading-In-A-Second-Dataset">Reading In A Second Dataset<a class="anchor-link" href="#Reading-In-A-Second-Dataset">¶</a></h1>
</div>
</div>
</div>
<div class="cell border-box-sizing code_cell rendered">
<div class="input">
<div class="prompt input_prompt">In [57]:</div>
<div class="inner_cell">
    <div class="input_area">
<div class=" highlight hl-ipython3"><pre><span></span><span class="kn">import</span> <span class="nn">csv</span>

<span class="k">with</span> <span class="nb">open</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="s2">"census.csv"</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="s2">"r"</span><span class="p">)</span> <span class="k">as</span> <span class="n">f</span><span class="p">:</span>
    <span class="n">reader</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">csv</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">reader</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">f</span><span class="p">)</span>
    <span class="n">census</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="nb">list</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">reader</span><span class="p">)</span>
    
<span class="n">census</span>
</pre></div>

    </div>
</div>
</div>

<div class="output_wrapper">
<div class="output">


<div class="output_area">

    <div class="prompt output_prompt">Out[57]:</div>




<div class="output_text output_subarea output_execute_result">
<pre>[['Id',

  'Two or More Races'],
 ['cen42010',
  'April 1, 2010 Census',
  'totsex',
  'Both Sexes',
  'tothisp',
  'Total',
  '0100000US',
  '',
  'United States',
  '308745538',
  '197318956',
  '44618105',
  '40250635',
  '3739506',
  '15159516',
  '674625',
  '6984195']]</pre>
</div>

</div>

</div>
</div>

</div>
<div class="cell border-box-sizing text_cell rendered"><div class="prompt input_prompt">
</div><div class="inner_cell">
<div class="text_cell_render border-box-sizing rendered_html">
<h1 id="Computing-Rates-Of-Gun-Deaths-Per-Race">Computing Rates Of Gun Deaths Per Race<a class="anchor-link" href="#Computing-Rates-Of-Gun-Deaths-Per-Race">¶</a></h1>
</div>
</div>
</div>
<div class="cell border-box-sizing code_cell rendered">
<div class="input">
<div class="prompt input_prompt">In [40]:</div>
<div class="inner_cell">
    <div class="input_area">
<div class=" highlight hl-ipython3"><pre><span></span><span class="n">mapping</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="p">{</span>
    <span class="s2">"Asian/Pacific Islander"</span><span class="p">:</span> <span class="mi">15159516</span> <span class="o">+</span> <span class="mi">674625</span><span class="p">,</span>
    <span class="s2">"Native American/Native Alaskan"</span><span class="p">:</span> <span class="mi">3739506</span><span class="p">,</span>
    <span class="s2">"Black"</span><span class="p">:</span> <span class="mi">40250635</span><span class="p">,</span>
    <span class="s2">"Hispanic"</span><span class="p">:</span> <span class="mi">44618105</span><span class="p">,</span>
    <span class="s2">"White"</span><span class="p">:</span> <span class="mi">197318956</span>
<span class="p">}</span>

<span class="n">race_per_hundredk</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="p">{}</span>
<span class="k">for</span> <span class="n">k</span><span class="p">,</span><span class="n">v</span> <span class="ow">in</span> <span class="n">race_counts</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">items</span><span class="p">():</span>
    <span class="n">race_per_hundredk</span><span class="p">[</span><span class="n">k</span><span class="p">]</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="p">(</span><span class="n">v</span> <span class="o">/</span> <span class="n">mapping</span><span class="p">[</span><span class="n">k</span><span class="p">])</span> <span class="o">*</span> <span class="mi">100000</span>

<span class="n">race_per_hundredk</span>
</pre></div>

    </div>
</div>
</div>

<div class="output_wrapper">
<div class="output">


<div class="output_area">

 'Black': 57.8773477735196,
 'Hispanic': 20.220491210910907,
 'Native American/Native Alaskan': 24.521955573811088,
 'White': 33.56849303419181}</pre>
</div>

</div>

</div>
</div>

</div>
<div class="cell border-box-sizing text_cell rendered"><div class="prompt input_prompt">
</div><div class="inner_cell">
<div class="text_cell_render border-box-sizing rendered_html">
<h1 id="Filtering-By-Intent">Filtering By Intent<a class="anchor-link" href="#Filtering-By-Intent">¶</a></h1>
</div>
</div>
</div>
<div class="cell border-box-sizing code_cell rendered">
<div class="input">
<div class="prompt input_prompt">In [41]:</div>
<div class="inner_cell">
    <div class="input_area">
<div class=" highlight hl-ipython3"><pre><span></span><span class="n">intents</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="p">[</span><span class="n">row</span><span class="p">[</span><span class="mi">3</span><span class="p">]</span> <span class="k">for</span> <span class="n">row</span> <span class="ow">in</span> <span class="n">data</span><span class="p">]</span>
<span class="n">homicide_race_counts</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="p">{}</span>
<span class="k">for</span> <span class="n">i</span><span class="p">,</span><span class="n">race</span> <span class="ow">in</span> <span class="nb">enumerate</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">races</span><span class="p">):</span>
    <span class="k">if</span> <span class="n">race</span> <span class="ow">not</span> <span class="ow">in</span> <span class="n">homicide_race_counts</span><span class="p">:</span>
        <span class="n">homicide_race_counts</span><span class="p">[</span><span class="n">race</span><span class="p">]</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="mi">0</span>
    <span class="k">if</span> <span class="n">intents</span><span class="p">[</span><span class="n">i</span><span class="p">]</span> <span class="o">==</span> <span class="s2">"Homicide"</span><span class="p">:</span>
        <span class="n">homicide_race_counts</span><span class="p">[</span><span class="n">race</span><span class="p">]</span> <span class="o">+=</span> <span class="mi">1</span>

<span class="n">race_per_hundredk</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="p">{}</span>
<span class="k">for</span> <span class="n">k</span><span class="p">,</span><span class="n">v</span> <span class="ow">in</span> <span class="n">homicide_race_counts</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">items</span><span class="p">():</span>
    <span class="n">race_per_hundredk</span><span class="p">[</span><span class="n">k</span><span class="p">]</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="p">(</span><span class="n">v</span> <span class="o">/</span> <span class="n">mapping</span><span class="p">[</span><span class="n">k</span><span class="p">])</span> <span class="o">*</span> <span class="mi">100000</span>

<span class="n">race_per_hundredk</span>     
</pre></div>

    </div>
</div>
</div>

<div class="output_wrapper">
<div class="output">


<div class="output_area">

    <div class="prompt output_prompt">Out[41]:</div>




<div class="output_text output_subarea output_execute_result">
<pre>{'Asian/Pacific Islander': 3.530346230970155,
 'Black': 48.471284987180944,
 'Hispanic': 12.627161104219914,
 'Native American/Native Alaskan': 8.717729026240365,
 'White': 4.6356417981453335}</pre>
</div>

</div>

</div>
</div>

</div>
<div class="cell border-box-sizing text_cell rendered"><div class="prompt input_prompt">
</div><div class="inner_cell">
<div class="text_cell_render border-box-sizing rendered_html">
<h2 id="Findings">Findings<a class="anchor-link" href="#Findings">¶</a></h2><p>It appears that gun related homicides in the US disproportionately affect people in the <code>Black</code> and <code>Hispanic</code> racial categories.</p>
<p>Some areas to investigate further:</p>
<ul>
<li>The link between month and homicide rate.</li>
<li>Homicide rate by gender.</li>
<li>The rates of other intents by gender and race.</li>
<li>Gun death rates by location and education.</li>
</ul>

</div>
</div>
</div>

<div class=" highlight hl-ipython3"><pre><span></span><span class="kn">import</span> <span class="nn">pandas</span> <span class="k">as</span> <span class="nn">pd</span>
<span class="n">pd</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">options</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">display</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">max_columns</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="mi">999</span>
<span class="kn">import</span> <span class="nn">numpy</span> <span class="k">as</span> <span class="nn">np</span>
<span class="kn">import</span> <span class="nn">matplotlib.pyplot</span> <span class="k">as</span> <span class="nn">plt</span>
<span class="kn">from</span> <span class="nn">sklearn.model_selection</span> <span class="kn">import</span> <span class="n">KFold</span>

<div class=" highlight hl-ipython3"><pre><span></span><span class="n">df</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">pd</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">read_csv</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="s2">"AmesHousing.tsv"</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">delimiter</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="s2">"</span><span class="se">\t</span><span class="s2">"</span><span class="p">)</span>

<div class="cell border-box-sizing code_cell rendered">
<div class="input">

<div class="inner_cell">
    <div class="input_area">
<div class=" highlight hl-ipython3"><pre><span></span><span class="k">def</span> <span class="nf">transform_features</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">df</span><span class="p">):</span>
    <span class="k">return</span> <span class="n">df</span>

<span class="k">def</span> <span class="nf">select_features</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">df</span><span class="p">):</span>
    <span class="k">return</span> <span class="n">df</span><span class="p">[[</span><span class="s2">"Gr Liv Area"</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="s2">"SalePrice"</span><span class="p">]]</span>

<span class="k">def</span> <span class="nf">train_and_test</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">df</span><span class="p">):</span>  
    <span class="n">train</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">df</span><span class="p">[:</span><span class="mi">1460</span><span class="p">]</span>
    <span class="n">test</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">df</span><span class="p">[</span><span class="mi">1460</span><span class="p">:]</span>
    
    <span class="c1">## You can use `pd.DataFrame.select_dtypes()` to specify column types</span>
    <span class="c1">## and return only those columns as a data frame.</span>
    <span class="n">numeric_train</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">train</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">select_dtypes</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">include</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="p">[</span><span class="s1">'integer'</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="s1">'float'</span><span class="p">])</span>
    <span class="n">numeric_test</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">test</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">select_dtypes</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">include</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="p">[</span><span class="s1">'integer'</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="s1">'float'</span><span class="p">])</span>
    
    <span class="c1">## You can use `pd.Series.drop()` to drop a value.</span>
    <span class="n">features</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">numeric_train</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">columns</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">drop</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="s2">"SalePrice"</span><span class="p">)</span>
    <span class="n">lr</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">linear_model</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">LinearRegression</span><span class="p">()</span>
    <span class="n">lr</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">fit</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">train</span><span class="p">[</span><span class="n">features</span><span class="p">],</span> <span class="n">train</span><span class="p">[</span><span class="s2">"SalePrice"</span><span class="p">])</span>
    <span class="n">predictions</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">lr</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">predict</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">test</span><span class="p">[</span><span class="n">features</span><span class="p">])</span>
    <span class="n">mse</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">mean_squared_error</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">test</span><span class="p">[</span><span class="s2">"SalePrice"</span><span class="p">],</span> <span class="n">predictions</span><span class="p">)</span>
    <span class="n">rmse</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">np</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">sqrt</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">mse</span><span class="p">)</span>
    
    <span class="k">return</span> <span class="n">rmse</span>

<span class="n">transform_df</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">transform_features</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">df</span><span class="p">)</span>
<span class="n">filtered_df</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">select_features</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">transform_df</span><span class="p">)</span>
<span class="n">rmse</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">train_and_test</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">filtered_df</span><span class="p">)</span>

<span class="n">rmse</span>
</pre></div>

<div class="cell border-box-sizing text_cell rendered"><div class="prompt input_prompt">
</div><div class="inner_cell">
<div class="text_cell_render border-box-sizing rendered_html">
<h2 id="Feature-Engineering">Feature Engineering<a class="anchor-link" href="#Feature-Engineering">¶</a></h2><ul>
<li>Handle missing values:<ul>
<li>All columns:<ul>
<li>Drop any with 5% or more missing values <strong>for now</strong>.</li>
</ul>
</li>
<li>Text columns:<ul>
<li>Drop any with 1 or more missing values <strong>for now</strong>.</li>
</ul>
</li>
<li>Numerical columns:<ul>
<li>For columns with missing values, fill in with the most common value in that column</li>
</ul>
</li>
</ul>
</li>
</ul>

</div>
</div>
</div>
<div class="cell border-box-sizing text_cell rendered"><div class="prompt input_prompt">
</div><div class="inner_cell">
<div class="text_cell_render border-box-sizing rendered_html">
<p>1: All columns: Drop any with 5% or more missing values <strong>for now</strong>.</p>

</div>
</div>
</div>
<div class="cell border-box-sizing code_cell rendered">
<div class="input">
<div class="prompt input_prompt">In [4]:</div>
<div class="inner_cell">
    <div class="input_area">
<div class=" highlight hl-ipython3"><pre><span></span><span class="c1">## Series object: column name -> number of missing values</span>
<span class="n">num_missing</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">df</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">isnull</span><span class="p">()</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">sum</span><span class="p">()</span>
</pre></div>

    </div>
</div>
</div>

</div>
<div class="cell border-box-sizing code_cell rendered">
<div class="input">
<div class="prompt input_prompt">In [5]:</div>
<div class="inner_cell">
    <div class="input_area">
<div class=" highlight hl-ipython3"><pre><span></span><span class="c1"># Filter Series to columns containing >5% missing values</span>
<span class="n">drop_missing_cols</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">num_missing</span><span class="p">[(</span><span class="n">num_missing</span> <span class="o">></span> <span class="nb">len</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">df</span><span class="p">)</span><span class="o">/</span><span class="mi">20</span><span class="p">)]</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">sort_values</span><span class="p">()</span>

<span class="c1"># Drop those columns from the data frame. Note the use of the .index accessor</span>
<span class="n">df</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">df</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">drop</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">drop_missing_cols</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">index</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">axis</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="mi">1</span><span class="p">)</span>
</pre></div>

    </div>
</div>
</div>

</div>
<div class="cell border-box-sizing text_cell rendered"><div class="prompt input_prompt">
</div><div class="inner_cell">
<div class="text_cell_render border-box-sizing rendered_html">
<p>2: Text columns: Drop any with 1 or more missing values <strong>for now</strong>.</p>

</div>
</div>
</div>
<div class="cell border-box-sizing code_cell rendered">
<div class="input">
<div class="prompt input_prompt">In [6]:</div>
<div class="inner_cell">
    <div class="input_area">
<div class=" highlight hl-ipython3"><pre><span></span><span class="c1">## Series object: column name -> number of missing values</span>
<span class="n">text_mv_counts</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">df</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">select_dtypes</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">include</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="p">[</span><span class="s1">'object'</span><span class="p">])</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">isnull</span><span class="p">()</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">sum</span><span class="p">()</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">sort_values</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">ascending</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="kc">False</span><span class="p">)</span>

<span class="c1">## Filter Series to columns containing *any* missing values</span>
<span class="n">drop_missing_cols_2</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">text_mv_counts</span><span class="p">[</span><span class="n">text_mv_counts</span> <span class="o">></span> <span class="mi">0</span><span class="p">]</span>

<span class="n">df</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">df</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">drop</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">drop_missing_cols_2</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">index</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">axis</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="mi">1</span><span class="p">)</span>
</pre></div>

    </div>
</div>
</div>

</div>
<div class="cell border-box-sizing text_cell rendered"><div class="prompt input_prompt">
</div><div class="inner_cell">
<div class="text_cell_render border-box-sizing rendered_html">
<p>3: Numerical columns: For columns with missing values, fill in with the most common value in that column</p>

</div>
</div>
</div>
<div class="cell border-box-sizing code_cell rendered">
<div class="input">

<div class=" highlight hl-ipython3"><pre><span></span><span class="c1">## Compute column-wise missing value counts</span>
<span class="n">num_missing</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">df</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">select_dtypes</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">include</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="p">[</span><span class="s1">'int'</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="s1">'float'</span><span class="p">])</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">isnull</span><span class="p">()</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">sum</span><span class="p">()</span>
<span class="n">fixable_numeric_cols</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">num_missing</span><span class="p">[(</span><span class="n">num_missing</span> <span class="o"><</span> <span class="nb">len</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">df</span><span class="p">)</span><span class="o">/</span><span class="mi">20</span><span class="p">)</span> <span class="o">&</span> <span class="p">(</span><span class="n">num_missing</span> <span class="o">></span> <span class="mi">0</span><span class="p">)]</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">sort_values</span><span class="p">()</span>
<span class="n">fixable_numeric_cols</span>
</pre></div>

    </div>
</div>
</div>

<div class=" highlight hl-ipython3"><pre><span></span><span class="c1">## Compute the most common value for each column in `fixable_nmeric_missing_cols`.</span>
<span class="n">replacement_values_dict</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">df</span><span class="p">[</span><span class="n">fixable_numeric_cols</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">index</span><span class="p">]</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">mode</span><span class="p">()</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">to_dict</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">orient</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="s1">'records'</span><span class="p">)[</span><span class="mi">0</span><span class="p">]</span>

<div class=" highlight hl-ipython3"><pre><span></span><span class="c1">## Create new columns</span>
<span class="n">df</span><span class="p">[</span><span class="s1">'Years Before Sale'</span><span class="p">]</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">years_sold</span>

<span class="n">df</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">df</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">drop</span><span class="p">([</span><span class="mi">1702</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="mi">2180</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="mi">2181</span><span class="p">],</span> <span class="n">axis</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="mi">0</span><span class="p">)</span>

</div><div class="inner_cell">
<div class="text_cell_render border-box-sizing rendered_html">
<p>Drop columns that:</p>
<ul>
<li>that aren't useful for ML</li>
<li>leak data about the final sale, read more about columns <a href="https://ww2.amstat.org/publications/jse/v19n3/decock/DataDocumentation.txt">here</a></li>
</ul>

</div>
</div>
</div>
<div class="cell border-box-sizing code_cell rendered">
<div class="input">

<div class="inner_cell">
    <div class="input_area">
<div class=" highlight hl-ipython3"><pre><span></span><span class="c1">## Drop columns that aren't useful for ML</span>
<span class="n">df</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">df</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">drop</span><span class="p">([</span><span class="s2">"PID"</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="s2">"Order"</span><span class="p">],</span> <span class="n">axis</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="mi">1</span><span class="p">)</span>

<span class="c1">## Drop columns that leak info about the final sale</span>

</div><div class="inner_cell">
<div class="text_cell_render border-box-sizing rendered_html">
<p>Let's update transform_features()</p>

</div>
</div>
</div>
<div class="cell border-box-sizing code_cell rendered">
<div class="input">
<div class="prompt input_prompt">In [15]:</div>
<div class="inner_cell">
    <div class="input_area">
<div class=" highlight hl-ipython3"><pre><span></span><span class="k">def</span> <span class="nf">transform_features</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">df</span><span class="p">):</span>
    <span class="n">num_missing</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">df</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">isnull</span><span class="p">()</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">sum</span><span class="p">()</span>
    <span class="n">drop_missing_cols</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">num_missing</span><span class="p">[(</span><span class="n">num_missing</span> <span class="o">></span> <span class="nb">len</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">df</span><span class="p">)</span><span class="o">/</span><span class="mi">20</span><span class="p">)]</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">sort_values</span><span class="p">()</span>
    <span class="n">df</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">df</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">drop</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">drop_missing_cols</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">index</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">axis</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="mi">1</span><span class="p">)</span>
    
    <span class="n">text_mv_counts</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">df</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">select_dtypes</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">include</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="p">[</span><span class="s1">'object'</span><span class="p">])</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">isnull</span><span class="p">()</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">sum</span><span class="p">()</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">sort_values</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">ascending</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="kc">False</span><span class="p">)</span>
    <span class="n">drop_missing_cols_2</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">text_mv_counts</span><span class="p">[</span><span class="n">text_mv_counts</span> <span class="o">></span> <span class="mi">0</span><span class="p">]</span>
    <span class="n">df</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">df</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">drop</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">drop_missing_cols_2</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">index</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">axis</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="mi">1</span><span class="p">)</span>
    
    <span class="n">num_missing</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">df</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">select_dtypes</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">include</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="p">[</span><span class="s1">'int'</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="s1">'float'</span><span class="p">])</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">isnull</span><span class="p">()</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">sum</span><span class="p">()</span>
    <span class="n">fixable_numeric_cols</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">num_missing</span><span class="p">[(</span><span class="n">num_missing</span> <span class="o"><</span> <span class="nb">len</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">df</span><span class="p">)</span><span class="o">/</span><span class="mi">20</span><span class="p">)</span> <span class="o">&</span> <span class="p">(</span><span class="n">num_missing</span> <span class="o">></span> <span class="mi">0</span><span class="p">)]</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">sort_values</span><span class="p">()</span>
    <span class="n">replacement_values_dict</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">df</span><span class="p">[</span><span class="n">fixable_numeric_cols</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">index</span><span class="p">]</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">mode</span><span class="p">()</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">to_dict</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">orient</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="s1">'records'</span><span class="p">)[</span><span class="mi">0</span><span class="p">]</span>
    <span class="n">df</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">df</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">fillna</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">replacement_values_dict</span><span class="p">)</span>
    
    <span class="n">years_sold</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">df</span><span class="p">[</span><span class="s1">'Yr Sold'</span><span class="p">]</span> <span class="o">-</span> <span class="n">df</span><span class="p">[</span><span class="s1">'Year Built'</span><span class="p">]</span>
    <span class="n">years_since_remod</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">df</span><span class="p">[</span><span class="s1">'Yr Sold'</span><span class="p">]</span> <span class="o">-</span> <span class="n">df</span><span class="p">[</span><span class="s1">'Year Remod/Add'</span><span class="p">]</span>
    <span class="n">df</span><span class="p">[</span><span class="s1">'Years Before Sale'</span><span class="p">]</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">years_sold</span>
    <span class="n">df</span><span class="p">[</span><span class="s1">'Years Since Remod'</span><span class="p">]</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">years_since_remod</span>
    <span class="n">df</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">df</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">drop</span><span class="p">([</span><span class="mi">1702</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="mi">2180</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="mi">2181</span><span class="p">],</span> <span class="n">axis</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="mi">0</span><span class="p">)</span>

    <span class="n">df</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">df</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">drop</span><span class="p">([</span><span class="s2">"PID"</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="s2">"Order"</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="s2">"Mo Sold"</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="s2">"Sale Condition"</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="s2">"Sale Type"</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="s2">"Year Built"</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="s2">"Year Remod/Add"</span><span class="p">],</span> <span class="n">axis</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="mi">1</span><span class="p">)</span>
    <span class="k">return</span> <span class="n">df</span>

<span class="k">def</span> <span class="nf">select_features</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">df</span><span class="p">):</span>
    <span class="k">return</span> <span class="n">df</span><span class="p">[[</span><span class="s2">"Gr Liv Area"</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="s2">"SalePrice"</span><span class="p">]]</span>

<span class="k">def</span> <span class="nf">train_and_test</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">df</span><span class="p">):</span>  
    <span class="n">train</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">df</span><span class="p">[:</span><span class="mi">1460</span><span class="p">]</span>
    <span class="n">test</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">df</span><span class="p">[</span><span class="mi">1460</span><span class="p">:]</span>
    
    <span class="c1">## You can use `pd.DataFrame.select_dtypes()` to specify column types</span>
    <span class="c1">## and return only those columns as a data frame.</span>
    <span class="n">numeric_train</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">train</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">select_dtypes</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">include</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="p">[</span><span class="s1">'integer'</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="s1">'float'</span><span class="p">])</span>
    <span class="n">numeric_test</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">test</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">select_dtypes</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">include</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="p">[</span><span class="s1">'integer'</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="s1">'float'</span><span class="p">])</span>
    
    <span class="c1">## You can use `pd.Series.drop()` to drop a value.</span>
    <span class="n">features</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">numeric_train</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">columns</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">drop</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="s2">"SalePrice"</span><span class="p">)</span>
    <span class="n">lr</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">linear_model</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">LinearRegression</span><span class="p">()</span>
    <span class="n">lr</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">fit</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">train</span><span class="p">[</span><span class="n">features</span><span class="p">],</span> <span class="n">train</span><span class="p">[</span><span class="s2">"SalePrice"</span><span class="p">])</span>
    <span class="n">predictions</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">lr</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">predict</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">test</span><span class="p">[</span><span class="n">features</span><span class="p">])</span>
    <span class="n">mse</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">mean_squared_error</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">test</span><span class="p">[</span><span class="s2">"SalePrice"</span><span class="p">],</span> <span class="n">predictions</span><span class="p">)</span>
    <span class="n">rmse</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">np</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">sqrt</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">mse</span><span class="p">)</span>
    
    <span class="k">return</span> <span class="n">rmse</span>

<span class="n">df</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">pd</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">read_csv</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="s2">"AmesHousing.tsv"</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">delimiter</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="s2">"</span><span class="se">\t</span><span class="s2">"</span><span class="p">)</span>
<span class="n">transform_df</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">transform_features</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">df</span><span class="p">)</span>
<span class="n">filtered_df</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">select_features</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">transform_df</span><span class="p">)</span>
<span class="n">rmse</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">train_and_test</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">filtered_df</span><span class="p">)</span>

<span class="n">rmse</span>
</pre></div>

                    <span class="s2">"Exterior 2nd"</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="s2">"Mas Vnr Type"</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="s2">"Foundation"</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="s2">"Heating"</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="s2">"Central Air"</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="s2">"Garage Type"</span><span class="p">,</span> 
                    <span class="s2">"Misc Feature"</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="s2">"Sale Type"</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="s2">"Sale Condition"</span><span class="p">]</span>

<div class="cell border-box-sizing text_cell rendered"><div class="prompt input_prompt">
</div><div class="inner_cell">
<div class="text_cell_render border-box-sizing rendered_html">
<ul>
<li>Which columns are currently numerical but need to be encoded as categorical instead (because the numbers don't have any semantic meaning)?</li>
<li>If a categorical column has hundreds of unique values (or categories), should we keep it? When we dummy code this column, hundreds of columns will need to be added back to the data frame.</li>
</ul>

</div>
</div>
</div>
<div class="cell border-box-sizing code_cell rendered">
<div class="input">
<div class="prompt input_prompt">In [21]:</div>
<div class="inner_cell">
    <div class="input_area">
<div class=" highlight hl-ipython3"><pre><span></span><span class="c1">## Which categorical columns have we still carried with us? We'll test tehse </span>
<span class="n">transform_cat_cols</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="p">[]</span>
<span class="k">for</span> <span class="n">col</span> <span class="ow">in</span> <span class="n">nominal_features</span><span class="p">:</span>
    <span class="k">if</span> <span class="n">col</span> <span class="ow">in</span> <span class="n">transform_df</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">columns</span><span class="p">:</span>
        <span class="n">transform_cat_cols</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">append</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">col</span><span class="p">)</span>

<span class="c1">## How many unique values in each categorical column?</span>
<span class="n">uniqueness_counts</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">transform_df</span><span class="p">[</span><span class="n">transform_cat_cols</span><span class="p">]</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">apply</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="k">lambda</span> <span class="n">col</span><span class="p">:</span> <span class="nb">len</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">col</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">value_counts</span><span class="p">()))</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">sort_values</span><span class="p">()</span>
<span class="c1">## Aribtrary cutoff of 10 unique values (worth experimenting)</span>
<span class="n">drop_nonuniq_cols</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">uniqueness_counts</span><span class="p">[</span><span class="n">uniqueness_counts</span> <span class="o">></span> <span class="mi">10</span><span class="p">]</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">index</span>
<span class="n">transform_df</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">transform_df</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">drop</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">drop_nonuniq_cols</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">axis</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="mi">1</span><span class="p">)</span>
</pre></div>

    </div>
</div>
</div>

</div>
<div class="cell border-box-sizing code_cell rendered">
<div class="input">
<div class="prompt input_prompt">In [22]:</div>
<div class="inner_cell">
    <div class="input_area">
<div class=" highlight hl-ipython3"><pre><span></span><span class="c1">## Select just the remaining text columns and convert to categorical</span>
<span class="n">text_cols</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">transform_df</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">select_dtypes</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">include</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="p">[</span><span class="s1">'object'</span><span class="p">])</span>
<span class="k">for</span> <span class="n">col</span> <span class="ow">in</span> <span class="n">text_cols</span><span class="p">:</span>
    <span class="n">transform_df</span><span class="p">[</span><span class="n">col</span><span class="p">]</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">transform_df</span><span class="p">[</span><span class="n">col</span><span class="p">]</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">astype</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="s1">'category'</span><span class="p">)</span>
    
<span class="c1">## Create dummy columns and add back to the dataframe!</span>
<span class="n">transform_df</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">pd</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">concat</span><span class="p">([</span>
    <span class="n">transform_df</span><span class="p">,</span> 
    <span class="n">pd</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">get_dummies</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">transform_df</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">select_dtypes</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">include</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="p">[</span><span class="s1">'category'</span><span class="p">]))</span>
<span class="p">],</span> <span class="n">axis</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="mi">1</span><span class="p">)</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">drop</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">text_cols</span><span class="p">,</span><span class="n">axis</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="mi">1</span><span class="p">)</span>
</pre></div>
